var book = {
	"name": "Acts",
	"numChapters": 28,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>In my former book,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26925A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26925A\"></sup> Theophilus, I wrote about all that Jesus began to do and to teach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26925B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26925B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>until the day he was taken up to heaven,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26926C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26926C\"></sup> after giving instructions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26926D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26926D\"></sup> through the Holy Spirit to the apostles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26926E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26926E\"></sup> he had chosen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26926F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26926F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>After his suffering, he presented himself to them and gave many convincing proofs that he was alive. He appeared to them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26927G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26927G\"></sup> over a period of forty days and spoke about the kingdom of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26927H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26927H\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>On one occasion, while he was eating with them, he gave them this command: <span class=\"woj\">“Do not leave Jerusalem, but wait<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26928I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26928I\"></sup> for the gift my Father promised, which you have heard me speak about.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26928J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26928J\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For John baptized with water,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26929K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26929K\"></sup> but in a few days you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26929L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26929L\"></sup></span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then they gathered around him and asked him, “Lord, are you at this time going to restore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26930M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26930M\"></sup> the kingdom to Israel?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He said to them: <span class=\"woj\">“It is not for you to know the times or dates the Father has set by his own authority.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26931N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26931N\"></sup></span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes on you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26932O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26932O\"></sup> and you will be my witnesses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26932P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26932P\"></sup> in Jerusalem, and in all Judea and Samaria,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26932Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26932Q\"></sup> and to the ends of the earth.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26932R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26932R\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>After he said this, he was taken up<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26933S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26933S\"></sup> before their very eyes, and a cloud hid him from their sight.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They were looking intently up into the sky as he was going, when suddenly two men dressed in white<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26934T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26934T\"></sup> stood beside them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Men of Galilee,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26935U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26935U\"></sup> they said, “why do you stand here looking into the sky? This same Jesus, who has been taken from you into heaven, will come back<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26935V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26935V\"></sup> in the same way you have seen him go into heaven.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the apostles returned to Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26936W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26936W\"></sup> from the hill called the Mount of Olives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26936X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26936X\"></sup> a Sabbath day’s walk from the city.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When they arrived, they went upstairs to the room<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26937Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26937Y\"></sup> where they were staying. Those present were Peter, John, James and Andrew; Philip and Thomas, Bartholomew and Matthew; James son of Alphaeus and Simon the Zealot, and Judas son of James.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26937Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26937Z\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They all joined together constantly in prayer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26938AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26938AA\"></sup> along with the women<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26938AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26938AB\"></sup> and Mary the mother of Jesus, and with his brothers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26938AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26938AC\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In those days Peter stood up among the believers (a group numbering about a hundred and twenty)",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and said, “Brothers and sisters,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26940AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26940AD\"></sup> the Scripture had to be fulfilled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26940AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26940AE\"></sup> in which the Holy Spirit spoke long ago through David concerning Judas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26940AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26940AF\"></sup> who served as guide for those who arrested Jesus.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He was one of our number<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26941AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26941AG\"></sup> and shared in our ministry.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26941AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26941AH\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>(With the payment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26942AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26942AI\"></sup> he received for his wickedness, Judas bought a field;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26942AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26942AJ\"></sup> there he fell headlong, his body burst open and all his intestines spilled out.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Everyone in Jerusalem heard about this, so they called that field in their language<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26943AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26943AK\"></sup> Akeldama, that is, Field of Blood.)",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“For,” said Peter, “it is written in the Book of Psalms:“‘May his place be deserted;let there be no one to dwell in it,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26944AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26944AL\"></sup>and,“‘May another take his place of leadership.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26944AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26944AM\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Therefore it is necessary to choose one of the men who have been with us the whole time the Lord Jesus was living among us,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>beginning from John’s baptism<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26946AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26946AN\"></sup> to the time when Jesus was taken up from us. For one of these must become a witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26946AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26946AO\"></sup> with us of his resurrection.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So they nominated two men: Joseph called Barsabbas (also known as Justus) and Matthias.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then they prayed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26948AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26948AP\"></sup> “Lord, you know everyone’s heart.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26948AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26948AQ\"></sup> Show us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26948AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26948AR\"></sup> which of these two you have chosen",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>to take over this apostolic ministry, which Judas left to go where he belongs.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then they cast lots, and the lot fell to Matthias; so he was added to the eleven apostles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26950AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26950AS\"></sup>"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>When the day of Pentecost<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26951A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26951A\"></sup> came, they were all together<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26951B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26951B\"></sup> in one place.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Suddenly a sound like the blowing of a violent wind came from heaven and filled the whole house where they were sitting.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26952C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26952C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They saw what seemed to be tongues of fire that separated and came to rest on each of them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>All of them were filled with the Holy Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26954D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26954D\"></sup> and began to speak in other tongues<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26954E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26954E\"></sup> as the Spirit enabled them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now there were staying in Jerusalem God-fearing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26955F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26955F\"></sup> Jews from every nation under heaven.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When they heard this sound, a crowd came together in bewilderment, because each one heard their own language being spoken.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Utterly amazed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26957G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26957G\"></sup> they asked: “Aren’t all these who are speaking Galileans?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26957H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26957H\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then how is it that each of us hears them in our native language?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Parthians, Medes and Elamites; residents of Mesopotamia, Judea and Cappadocia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26959I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26959I\"></sup> Pontus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26959J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26959J\"></sup> and Asia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26959K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26959K\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Phrygia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26960L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26960L\"></sup> and Pamphylia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26960M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26960M\"></sup> Egypt and the parts of Libya near Cyrene;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26960N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26960N\"></sup> visitors from Rome",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>(both Jews and converts to Judaism); Cretans and Arabs—we hear them declaring the wonders of God in our own tongues!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Amazed and perplexed, they asked one another, “What does this mean?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Some, however, made fun of them and said, “They have had too much wine.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26963O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26963O\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Peter stood up with the Eleven, raised his voice and addressed the crowd: “Fellow Jews and all of you who live in Jerusalem, let me explain this to you; listen carefully to what I say.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>These people are not drunk, as you suppose. It’s only nine in the morning!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26965P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26965P\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>No, this is what was spoken by the prophet Joel:",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“‘In the last days, God says,I will pour out my Spirit on all people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26967Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26967Q\"></sup>Your sons and daughters will prophesy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26967R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26967R\"></sup>your young men will see visions,your old men will dream dreams.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Even on my servants, both men and women,I will pour out my Spirit in those days,and they will prophesy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26968S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26968S\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I will show wonders in the heavens aboveand signs on the earth below,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26969T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26969T\"></sup>blood and fire and billows of smoke.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The sun will be turned to darknessand the moon to blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26970U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26970U\"></sup>before the coming of the great and glorious day of the Lord.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And everyone who callson the name of the Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26971V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26971V\"></sup> will be saved.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26971W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26971W\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Fellow Israelites, listen to this: Jesus of Nazareth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26972X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26972X\"></sup> was a man accredited by God to you by miracles, wonders and signs,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26972Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26972Y\"></sup> which God did among you through him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26972Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26972Z\"></sup> as you yourselves know.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>This man was handed over to you by God’s deliberate plan and foreknowledge;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26973AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26973AA\"></sup> and you, with the help of wicked men, put him to death by nailing him to the cross.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26973AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26973AB\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But God raised him from the dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26974AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26974AC\"></sup> freeing him from the agony of death, because it was impossible for death to keep its hold on him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26974AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26974AD\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>David said about him:“‘I saw the Lord always before me.Because he is at my right hand,I will not be shaken.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Therefore my heart is glad and my tongue rejoices;my body also will rest in hope,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>because you will not abandon me to the realm of the dead,you will not let your holy one see decay.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26977AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26977AE\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You have made known to me the paths of life;you will fill me with joy in your presence.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26978AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26978AF\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Fellow Israelites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26979AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26979AG\"></sup> I can tell you confidently that the patriarch<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26979AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26979AH\"></sup> David died and was buried,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26979AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26979AI\"></sup> and his tomb is here<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26979AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26979AJ\"></sup> to this day.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But he was a prophet and knew that God had promised him on oath that he would place one of his descendants on his throne.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26980AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26980AK\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Seeing what was to come, he spoke of the resurrection of the Messiah, that he was not abandoned to the realm of the dead, nor did his body see decay.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26981AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26981AL\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>God has raised this Jesus to life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26982AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26982AM\"></sup> and we are all witnesses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26982AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26982AN\"></sup> of it.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Exalted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26983AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26983AO\"></sup> to the right hand of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26983AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26983AP\"></sup> he has received from the Father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26983AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26983AQ\"></sup> the promised Holy Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26983AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26983AR\"></sup> and has poured out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26983AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26983AS\"></sup> what you now see and hear.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>For David did not ascend to heaven, and yet he said,“‘The Lord said to my Lord:“Sit at my right hand",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>until I make your enemiesa footstool for your feet.”’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26985AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26985AT\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“Therefore let all Israel be assured of this: God has made this Jesus, whom you crucified, both Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26986AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26986AU\"></sup> and Messiah.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26986AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26986AV\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>When the people heard this, they were cut to the heart and said to Peter and the other apostles, “Brothers, what shall we do?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26987AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26987AW\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Peter replied, “Repent and be baptized,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26988AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26988AX\"></sup> every one of you, in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26988AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26988AY\"></sup> And you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26988AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26988AZ\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The promise is for you and your children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26989BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26989BA\"></sup> and for all who are far off<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26989BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26989BB\"></sup>—for all whom the Lord our God will call.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>With many other words he warned them; and he pleaded with them, “Save yourselves from this corrupt generation.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26990BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26990BC\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Those who accepted his message were baptized, and about three thousand were added to their number<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26991BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26991BD\"></sup> that day.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>They devoted themselves to the apostles’ teaching<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26992BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26992BE\"></sup> and to fellowship, to the breaking of bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26992BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26992BF\"></sup> and to prayer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26992BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26992BG\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Everyone was filled with awe at the many wonders and signs performed by the apostles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26993BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26993BH\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>All the believers were together and had everything in common.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26994BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26994BI\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>They sold property and possessions to give to anyone who had need.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26995BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26995BJ\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Every day they continued to meet together in the temple courts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26996BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26996BK\"></sup> They broke bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26996BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26996BL\"></sup> in their homes and ate together with glad and sincere hearts,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>praising God and enjoying the favor of all the people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26997BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26997BM\"></sup> And the Lord added to their number<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26997BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26997BN\"></sup> daily those who were being saved."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>One day Peter and John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26998A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26998A\"></sup> were going up to the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26998B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26998B\"></sup> at the time of prayer—at three in the afternoon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26998C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26998C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now a man who was lame from birth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26999D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26999D\"></sup> was being carried to the temple gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26999E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26999E\"></sup> called Beautiful, where he was put every day to beg<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26999F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26999F\"></sup> from those going into the temple courts.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When he saw Peter and John about to enter, he asked them for money.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Peter looked straight at him, as did John. Then Peter said, “Look at us!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the man gave them his attention, expecting to get something from them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Peter said, “Silver or gold I do not have, but what I do have I give you. In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27003G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27003G\"></sup> walk.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Taking him by the right hand, he helped him up, and instantly the man’s feet and ankles became strong.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He jumped to his feet and began to walk. Then he went with them into the temple courts, walking and jumping,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27005H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27005H\"></sup> and praising God.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When all the people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27006I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27006I\"></sup> saw him walking and praising God,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>they recognized him as the same man who used to sit begging at the temple gate called Beautiful,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27007J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27007J\"></sup> and they were filled with wonder and amazement at what had happened to him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>While the man held on to Peter and John,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27008K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27008K\"></sup> all the people were astonished and came running to them in the place called Solomon’s Colonnade.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27008L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27008L\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Peter saw this, he said to them: “Fellow Israelites, why does this surprise you? Why do you stare at us as if by our own power or godliness we had made this man walk?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The God of Abraham, Isaac and Jacob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27010M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27010M\"></sup> the God of our fathers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27010N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27010N\"></sup> has glorified his servant Jesus. You handed him over<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27010O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27010O\"></sup> to be killed, and you disowned him before Pilate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27010P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27010P\"></sup> though he had decided to let him go.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27010Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27010Q\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You disowned the Holy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27011R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27011R\"></sup> and Righteous One<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27011S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27011S\"></sup> and asked that a murderer be released to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27011T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27011T\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You killed the author of life, but God raised him from the dead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27012U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27012U\"></sup> We are witnesses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27012V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27012V\"></sup> of this.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>By faith in the name of Jesus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27013W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27013W\"></sup> this man whom you see and know was made strong. It is Jesus’ name and the faith that comes through him that has completely healed him, as you can all see.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Now, fellow Israelites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27014X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27014X\"></sup> I know that you acted in ignorance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27014Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27014Y\"></sup> as did your leaders.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27014Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27014Z\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But this is how God fulfilled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27015AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27015AA\"></sup> what he had foretold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27015AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27015AB\"></sup> through all the prophets,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27015AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27015AC\"></sup> saying that his Messiah would suffer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27015AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27015AD\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Repent, then, and turn to God, so that your sins may be wiped out,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27016AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27016AE\"></sup> that times of refreshing may come from the Lord,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and that he may send the Messiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27017AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27017AF\"></sup> who has been appointed for you—even Jesus.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Heaven must receive him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27018AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27018AG\"></sup> until the time comes for God to restore everything,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27018AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27018AH\"></sup> as he promised long ago through his holy prophets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27018AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27018AI\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For Moses said, ‘The Lord your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from among your own people; you must listen to everything he tells you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27019AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27019AJ\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Anyone who does not listen to him will be completely cut off from their people.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27020AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27020AK\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Indeed, beginning with Samuel, all the prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27021AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27021AL\"></sup> who have spoken have foretold these days.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And you are heirs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27022AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27022AM\"></sup> of the prophets and of the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27022AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27022AN\"></sup> God made with your fathers. He said to Abraham, ‘Through your offspring all peoples on earth will be blessed.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27022AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27022AO\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When God raised up<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27023AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27023AP\"></sup> his servant, he sent him first<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27023AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27023AQ\"></sup> to you to bless you by turning each of you from your wicked ways.”"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>The priests and the captain of the temple guard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27024A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27024A\"></sup> and the Sadducees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27024B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27024B\"></sup> came up to Peter and John while they were speaking to the people.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They were greatly disturbed because the apostles were teaching the people, proclaiming in Jesus the resurrection of the dead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27025C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27025C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They seized Peter and John and, because it was evening, they put them in jail<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27026D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27026D\"></sup> until the next day.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But many who heard the message believed; so the number of men who believed grew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27027E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27027E\"></sup> to about five thousand.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The next day the rulers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27028F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27028F\"></sup> the elders and the teachers of the law met in Jerusalem.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Annas the high priest was there, and so were Caiaphas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27029G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27029G\"></sup> John, Alexander and others of the high priest’s family.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They had Peter and John brought before them and began to question them: “By what power or what name did you do this?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Peter, filled with the Holy Spirit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27031H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27031H\"></sup> said to them: “Rulers and elders of the people!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27031I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27031I\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If we are being called to account today for an act of kindness shown to a man who was lame<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27032J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27032J\"></sup> and are being asked how he was healed,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>then know this, you and all the people of Israel: It is by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27033K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27033K\"></sup> whom you crucified but whom God raised from the dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27033L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27033L\"></sup> that this man stands before you healed.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jesus is“‘the stone you builders rejected,which has become the cornerstone.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27034M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27034M\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Salvation is found in no one else, for there is no other name under heaven given to mankind by which we must be saved.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27035N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27035N\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When they saw the courage of Peter and John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27036O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27036O\"></sup> and realized that they were unschooled, ordinary men,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27036P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27036P\"></sup> they were astonished and they took note that these men had been with Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27036Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27036Q\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But since they could see the man who had been healed standing there with them, there was nothing they could say.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they ordered them to withdraw from the Sanhedrin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27038R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27038R\"></sup> and then conferred together.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“What are we going to do with these men?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27039S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27039S\"></sup> they asked. “Everyone living in Jerusalem knows they have performed a notable sign,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27039T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27039T\"></sup> and we cannot deny it.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But to stop this thing from spreading any further among the people, we must warn them to speak no longer to anyone in this name.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then they called them in again and commanded them not to speak or teach at all in the name of Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27041U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27041U\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But Peter and John replied, “Which is right in God’s eyes: to listen to you, or to him?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27042V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27042V\"></sup> You be the judges!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for us, we cannot help speaking<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27043W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27043W\"></sup> about what we have seen and heard.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27043X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27043X\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>After further threats they let them go. They could not decide how to punish them, because all the people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27044Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27044Y\"></sup> were praising God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27044Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27044Z\"></sup> for what had happened.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For the man who was miraculously healed was over forty years old.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>On their release, Peter and John went back to their own people and reported all that the chief priests and the elders had said to them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When they heard this, they raised their voices together in prayer to God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27047AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27047AA\"></sup> “Sovereign Lord,” they said, “you made the heavens and the earth and the sea, and everything in them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27047AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27047AB\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You spoke by the Holy Spirit through the mouth of your servant, our father David:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27048AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27048AC\"></sup>“‘Why do the nations rageand the peoples plot in vain?",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The kings of the earth rise upand the rulers band togetheragainst the Lordand against his anointed one.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27049AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27049AD\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Indeed Herod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27050AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27050AE\"></sup> and Pontius Pilate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27050AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27050AF\"></sup> met together with the Gentiles and the people of Israel in this city to conspire against your holy servant Jesus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27050AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27050AG\"></sup> whom you anointed.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They did what your power and will had decided beforehand should happen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27051AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27051AH\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now, Lord, consider their threats and enable your servants to speak your word with great boldness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27052AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27052AI\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Stretch out your hand to heal and perform signs and wonders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27053AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27053AJ\"></sup> through the name of your holy servant Jesus.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27053AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27053AK\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>After they prayed, the place where they were meeting was shaken.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27054AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27054AL\"></sup> And they were all filled with the Holy Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27054AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27054AM\"></sup> and spoke the word of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27054AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27054AN\"></sup> boldly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27054AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27054AO\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>All the believers were one in heart and mind. No one claimed that any of their possessions was their own, but they shared everything they had.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27055AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27055AP\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>With great power the apostles continued to testify<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27056AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27056AQ\"></sup> to the resurrection<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27056AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27056AR\"></sup> of the Lord Jesus. And God’s grace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27056AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27056AS\"></sup> was so powerfully at work in them all",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>that there were no needy persons among them. For from time to time those who owned land or houses sold them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27057AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27057AT\"></sup> brought the money from the sales",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and put it at the apostles’ feet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27058AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27058AU\"></sup> and it was distributed to anyone who had need.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27058AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27058AV\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Joseph, a Levite from Cyprus, whom the apostles called Barnabas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27059AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27059AW\"></sup> (which means “son of encouragement”),",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>sold a field he owned and brought the money and put it at the apostles’ feet.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27060AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27060AX\"></sup>"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Now a man named Ananias, together with his wife Sapphira, also sold a piece of property.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>With his wife’s full knowledge he kept back part of the money for himself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27062A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27062A\"></sup> but brought the rest and put it at the apostles’ feet.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27062B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27062B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Peter said, “Ananias, how is it that Satan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27063C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27063C\"></sup> has so filled your heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27063D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27063D\"></sup> that you have lied to the Holy Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27063E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27063E\"></sup> and have kept for yourself some of the money you received for the land?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27063F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27063F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Didn’t it belong to you before it was sold? And after it was sold, wasn’t the money at your disposal?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27064G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27064G\"></sup> What made you think of doing such a thing? You have not lied just to human beings but to God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27064H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27064H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Ananias heard this, he fell down and died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27065I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27065I\"></sup> And great fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27065J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27065J\"></sup> seized all who heard what had happened.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then some young men came forward, wrapped up his body,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27066K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27066K\"></sup> and carried him out and buried him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>About three hours later his wife came in, not knowing what had happened.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Peter asked her, “Tell me, is this the price you and Ananias got for the land?”“Yes,” she said, “that is the price.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27068L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27068L\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Peter said to her, “How could you conspire to test the Spirit of the Lord?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27069M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27069M\"></sup> Listen! The feet of the men who buried your husband are at the door, and they will carry you out also.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>At that moment she fell down at his feet and died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27070N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27070N\"></sup> Then the young men came in and, finding her dead, carried her out and buried her beside her husband.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27070O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27070O\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Great fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27071P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27071P\"></sup> seized the whole church and all who heard about these events.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The apostles performed many signs and wonders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27072Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27072Q\"></sup> among the people. And all the believers used to meet together<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27072R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27072R\"></sup> in Solomon’s Colonnade.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27072S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27072S\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>No one else dared join them, even though they were highly regarded by the people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27073T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27073T\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Nevertheless, more and more men and women believed in the Lord and were added to their number.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27074U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27074U\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As a result, people brought the sick into the streets and laid them on beds and mats so that at least Peter’s shadow might fall on some of them as he passed by.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27075V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27075V\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Crowds gathered also from the towns around Jerusalem, bringing their sick and those tormented by impure spirits, and all of them were healed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27076W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27076W\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the high priest and all his associates, who were members of the party<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27077X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27077X\"></sup> of the Sadducees,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27077Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27077Y\"></sup> were filled with jealousy.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They arrested the apostles and put them in the public jail.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27078Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27078Z\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But during the night an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27079AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27079AA\"></sup> of the Lord opened the doors of the jail<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27079AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27079AB\"></sup> and brought them out.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27079AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27079AC\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Go, stand in the temple courts,” he said, “and tell the people all about this new life.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27080AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27080AD\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>At daybreak they entered the temple courts, as they had been told, and began to teach the people.When the high priest and his associates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27081AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27081AE\"></sup> arrived, they called together the Sanhedrin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27081AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27081AF\"></sup>—the full assembly of the elders of Israel—and sent to the jail for the apostles.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But on arriving at the jail, the officers did not find them there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27082AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27082AG\"></sup> So they went back and reported,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“We found the jail securely locked, with the guards standing at the doors; but when we opened them, we found no one inside.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>On hearing this report, the captain of the temple guard and the chief priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27084AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27084AH\"></sup> were at a loss, wondering what this might lead to.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then someone came and said, “Look! The men you put in jail are standing in the temple courts teaching the people.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>At that, the captain went with his officers and brought the apostles. They did not use force, because they feared that the people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27086AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27086AI\"></sup> would stone them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The apostles were brought in and made to appear before the Sanhedrin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27087AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27087AJ\"></sup> to be questioned by the high priest.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“We gave you strict orders not to teach in this name,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27088AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27088AK\"></sup> he said. “Yet you have filled Jerusalem with your teaching and are determined to make us guilty of this man’s blood.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27088AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27088AL\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Peter and the other apostles replied: “We must obey God rather than human beings!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27089AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27089AM\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The God of our ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27090AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27090AN\"></sup> raised Jesus from the dead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27090AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27090AO\"></sup>—whom you killed by hanging him on a cross.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27090AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27090AP\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>God exalted him to his own right hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27091AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27091AQ\"></sup> as Prince and Savior<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27091AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27091AR\"></sup> that he might bring Israel to repentance and forgive their sins.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27091AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27091AS\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>We are witnesses of these things,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27092AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27092AT\"></sup> and so is the Holy Spirit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27092AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27092AU\"></sup> whom God has given to those who obey him.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When they heard this, they were furious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27093AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27093AV\"></sup> and wanted to put them to death.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But a Pharisee named Gamaliel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27094AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27094AW\"></sup> a teacher of the law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27094AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27094AX\"></sup> who was honored by all the people, stood up in the Sanhedrin and ordered that the men be put outside for a little while.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then he addressed the Sanhedrin: “Men of Israel, consider carefully what you intend to do to these men.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Some time ago Theudas appeared, claiming to be somebody, and about four hundred men rallied to him. He was killed, all his followers were dispersed, and it all came to nothing.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>After him, Judas the Galilean appeared in the days of the census<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27097AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27097AY\"></sup> and led a band of people in revolt. He too was killed, and all his followers were scattered.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Therefore, in the present case I advise you: Leave these men alone! Let them go! For if their purpose or activity is of human origin, it will fail.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27098AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27098AZ\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>But if it is from God, you will not be able to stop these men; you will only find yourselves fighting against God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27099BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27099BA\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>His speech persuaded them. They called the apostles in and had them flogged.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27100BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27100BB\"></sup> Then they ordered them not to speak in the name of Jesus, and let them go.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The apostles left the Sanhedrin, rejoicing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27101BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27101BC\"></sup> because they had been counted worthy of suffering disgrace for the Name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27101BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27101BD\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Day after day, in the temple courts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27102BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27102BE\"></sup> and from house to house, they never stopped teaching and proclaiming the good news<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27102BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27102BF\"></sup> that Jesus is the Messiah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27102BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27102BG\"></sup>"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>In those days when the number of disciples was increasing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27103A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27103A\"></sup> the Hellenistic Jews<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27103B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27103B\"></sup> among them complained against the Hebraic Jews because their widows<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27103C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27103C\"></sup> were being overlooked in the daily distribution of food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27103D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27103D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the Twelve gathered all the disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27104E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27104E\"></sup> together and said, “It would not be right for us to neglect the ministry of the word of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27104F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27104F\"></sup> in order to wait on tables.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Brothers and sisters,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27105G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27105G\"></sup> choose seven men from among you who are known to be full of the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27105H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27105H\"></sup> and wisdom. We will turn this responsibility over to them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27105I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27105I\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and will give our attention to prayer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27106J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27106J\"></sup> and the ministry of the word.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>This proposal pleased the whole group. They chose Stephen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27107K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27107K\"></sup> a man full of faith and of the Holy Spirit;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27107L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27107L\"></sup> also Philip,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27107M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27107M\"></sup> Procorus, Nicanor, Timon, Parmenas, and Nicolas from Antioch, a convert to Judaism.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They presented these men to the apostles, who prayed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27108N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27108N\"></sup> and laid their hands on them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27108O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27108O\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So the word of God spread.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27109P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27109P\"></sup> The number of disciples in Jerusalem increased rapidly,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27109Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27109Q\"></sup> and a large number of priests became obedient to the faith.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now Stephen, a man full of God’s grace and power, performed great wonders and signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27110R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27110R\"></sup> among the people.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Opposition arose, however, from members of the Synagogue of the Freedmen (as it was called)—Jews of Cyrene<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27111S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27111S\"></sup> and Alexandria as well as the provinces of Cilicia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27111T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27111T\"></sup> and Asia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27111U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27111U\"></sup>—who began to argue with Stephen.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But they could not stand up against the wisdom the Spirit gave him as he spoke.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27112V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27112V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then they secretly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27113W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27113W\"></sup> persuaded some men to say, “We have heard Stephen speak blasphemous words against Moses and against God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27113X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27113X\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So they stirred up the people and the elders and the teachers of the law. They seized Stephen and brought him before the Sanhedrin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27114Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27114Y\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They produced false witnesses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27115Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27115Z\"></sup> who testified, “This fellow never stops speaking against this holy place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27115AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27115AA\"></sup> and against the law.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For we have heard him say that this Jesus of Nazareth will destroy this place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27116AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27116AB\"></sup> and change the customs Moses handed down to us.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27116AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27116AC\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>All who were sitting in the Sanhedrin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27117AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27117AD\"></sup> looked intently at Stephen, and they saw that his face was like the face of an angel."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Then the high priest asked Stephen, “Are these charges true?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>To this he replied: “Brothers and fathers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27119A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27119A\"></sup> listen to me! The God of glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27119B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27119B\"></sup> appeared to our father Abraham while he was still in Mesopotamia, before he lived in Harran.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27119C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27119C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>‘Leave your country and your people,’ God said, ‘and go to the land I will show you.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27120D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27120D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“So he left the land of the Chaldeans and settled in Harran. After the death of his father, God sent him to this land where you are now living.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27121E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27121E\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He gave him no inheritance here,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27122F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27122F\"></sup> not even enough ground to set his foot on. But God promised him that he and his descendants after him would possess the land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27122G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27122G\"></sup> even though at that time Abraham had no child.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>God spoke to him in this way: ‘For four hundred years your descendants will be strangers in a country not their own, and they will be enslaved and mistreated.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27123H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27123H\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But I will punish the nation they serve as slaves,’ God said, ‘and afterward they will come out of that country and worship me in this place.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27124I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27124I\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then he gave Abraham the covenant of circumcision.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27125J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27125J\"></sup> And Abraham became the father of Isaac and circumcised him eight days after his birth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27125K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27125K\"></sup> Later Isaac became the father of Jacob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27125L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27125L\"></sup> and Jacob became the father of the twelve patriarchs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27125M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27125M\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Because the patriarchs were jealous of Joseph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27126N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27126N\"></sup> they sold him as a slave into Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27126O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27126O\"></sup> But God was with him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27126P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27126P\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and rescued him from all his troubles. He gave Joseph wisdom and enabled him to gain the goodwill of Pharaoh king of Egypt. So Pharaoh made him ruler over Egypt and all his palace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27127Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27127Q\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Then a famine struck all Egypt and Canaan, bringing great suffering, and our ancestors could not find food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27128R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27128R\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Jacob heard that there was grain in Egypt, he sent our forefathers on their first visit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27129S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27129S\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>On their second visit, Joseph told his brothers who he was,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27130T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27130T\"></sup> and Pharaoh learned about Joseph’s family.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27130U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27130U\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After this, Joseph sent for his father Jacob and his whole family,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27131V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27131V\"></sup> seventy-five in all.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27131W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27131W\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Jacob went down to Egypt, where he and our ancestors died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27132X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27132X\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Their bodies were brought back to Shechem and placed in the tomb that Abraham had bought from the sons of Hamor at Shechem for a certain sum of money.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27133Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27133Y\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“As the time drew near for God to fulfill his promise to Abraham, the number of our people in Egypt had greatly increased.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27134Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27134Z\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then ‘a new king, to whom Joseph meant nothing, came to power in Egypt.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27135AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27135AA\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He dealt treacherously with our people and oppressed our ancestors by forcing them to throw out their newborn babies so that they would die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27136AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27136AB\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“At that time Moses was born, and he was no ordinary child. For three months he was cared for by his family.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27137AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27137AC\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When he was placed outside, Pharaoh’s daughter took him and brought him up as her own son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27138AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27138AD\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Moses was educated in all the wisdom of the Egyptians<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27139AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27139AE\"></sup> and was powerful in speech and action.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“When Moses was forty years old, he decided to visit his own people, the Israelites.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He saw one of them being mistreated by an Egyptian, so he went to his defense and avenged him by killing the Egyptian.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Moses thought that his own people would realize that God was using him to rescue them, but they did not.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The next day Moses came upon two Israelites who were fighting. He tried to reconcile them by saying, ‘Men, you are brothers; why do you want to hurt each other?’",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“But the man who was mistreating the other pushed Moses aside and said, ‘Who made you ruler and judge over us?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27144AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27144AF\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Are you thinking of killing me as you killed the Egyptian yesterday?’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When Moses heard this, he fled to Midian, where he settled as a foreigner and had two sons.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27146AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27146AG\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“After forty years had passed, an angel appeared to Moses in the flames of a burning bush in the desert near Mount Sinai.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>When he saw this, he was amazed at the sight. As he went over to get a closer look, he heard the Lord say:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27148AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27148AH\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>‘I am the God of your fathers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27149AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27149AI\"></sup> the God of Abraham, Isaac and Jacob.’ Moses trembled with fear and did not dare to look.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27149AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27149AJ\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“Then the Lord said to him, ‘Take off your sandals, for the place where you are standing is holy ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27150AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27150AK\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>I have indeed seen the oppression of my people in Egypt. I have heard their groaning and have come down to set them free. Now come, I will send you back to Egypt.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27151AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27151AL\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“This is the same Moses they had rejected with the words, ‘Who made you ruler and judge?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27152AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27152AM\"></sup> He was sent to be their ruler and deliverer by God himself, through the angel who appeared to him in the bush.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He led them out of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27153AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27153AN\"></sup> and performed wonders and signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27153AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27153AO\"></sup> in Egypt, at the Red Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27153AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27153AP\"></sup> and for forty years in the wilderness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27153AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27153AQ\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“This is the Moses who told the Israelites, ‘God will raise up for you a prophet like me from your own people.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27154AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27154AR\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>He was in the assembly in the wilderness, with the angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27155AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27155AS\"></sup> who spoke to him on Mount Sinai, and with our ancestors;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27155AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27155AT\"></sup> and he received living words<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27155AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27155AU\"></sup> to pass on to us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27155AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27155AV\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“But our ancestors refused to obey him. Instead, they rejected him and in their hearts turned back to Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27156AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27156AW\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>They told Aaron, ‘Make us gods who will go before us. As for this fellow Moses who led us out of Egypt—we don’t know what has happened to him!’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27157AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27157AX\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>That was the time they made an idol in the form of a calf. They brought sacrifices to it and reveled in what their own hands had made.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27158AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27158AY\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>But God turned away from them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27159AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27159AZ\"></sup> and gave them over to the worship of the sun, moon and stars.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27159BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27159BA\"></sup> This agrees with what is written in the book of the prophets:“‘Did you bring me sacrifices and offeringsforty years in the wilderness, people of Israel?",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>You have taken up the tabernacle of Molekand the star of your god Rephan,the idols you made to worship.Therefore I will send you into exile’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27160BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27160BB\"></sup> beyond Babylon.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“Our ancestors had the tabernacle of the covenant law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27161BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27161BC\"></sup> with them in the wilderness. It had been made as God directed Moses, according to the pattern he had seen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27161BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27161BD\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>After receiving the tabernacle, our ancestors under Joshua brought it with them when they took the land from the nations God drove out before them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27162BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27162BE\"></sup> It remained in the land until the time of David,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27162BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27162BF\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>who enjoyed God’s favor and asked that he might provide a dwelling place for the God of Jacob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27163BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27163BG\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>But it was Solomon who built a house for him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27164BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27164BH\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>“However, the Most High<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27165BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27165BI\"></sup> does not live in houses made by human hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27165BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27165BJ\"></sup> As the prophet says:",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“‘Heaven is my throne,and the earth is my footstool.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27166BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27166BK\"></sup>What kind of house will you build for me?says the Lord.Or where will my resting place be?",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Has not my hand made all these things?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27167BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27167BL\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>“You stiff-necked people!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27168BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27168BM\"></sup> Your hearts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27168BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27168BN\"></sup> and ears are still uncircumcised. You are just like your ancestors: You always resist the Holy Spirit!",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Was there ever a prophet your ancestors did not persecute?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27169BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27169BO\"></sup> They even killed those who predicted the coming of the Righteous One. And now you have betrayed and murdered him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27169BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27169BP\"></sup>—",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>you who have received the law that was given through angels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27170BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27170BQ\"></sup> but have not obeyed it.”",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>When the members of the Sanhedrin heard this, they were furious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27171BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27171BR\"></sup> and gnashed their teeth at him.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>But Stephen, full of the Holy Spirit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27172BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27172BS\"></sup> looked up to heaven and saw the glory of God, and Jesus standing at the right hand of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27172BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27172BT\"></sup>",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>“Look,” he said, “I see heaven open<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27173BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27173BU\"></sup> and the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27173BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27173BV\"></sup> standing at the right hand of God.”",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>At this they covered their ears and, yelling at the top of their voices, they all rushed at him,",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>dragged him out of the city<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27175BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27175BW\"></sup> and began to stone him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27175BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27175BX\"></sup> Meanwhile, the witnesses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27175BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27175BY\"></sup> laid their coats<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27175BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27175BZ\"></sup> at the feet of a young man named Saul.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27175CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27175CA\"></sup>",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>While they were stoning him, Stephen prayed, “Lord Jesus, receive my spirit.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27176CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27176CB\"></sup>",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>Then he fell on his knees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27177CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27177CC\"></sup> and cried out, “Lord, do not hold this sin against them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27177CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27177CD\"></sup> When he had said this, he fell asleep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27177CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27177CE\"></sup>"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>And Saul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27178A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27178A\"></sup> approved of their killing him.On that day a great persecution broke out against the church in Jerusalem, and all except the apostles were scattered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27178B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27178B\"></sup> throughout Judea and Samaria.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27178C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27178C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Godly men buried Stephen and mourned deeply for him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Saul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27180D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27180D\"></sup> began to destroy the church.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27180E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27180E\"></sup> Going from house to house, he dragged off both men and women and put them in prison.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Those who had been scattered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27181F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27181F\"></sup> preached the word wherever they went.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27181G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27181G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Philip<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27182H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27182H\"></sup> went down to a city in Samaria and proclaimed the Messiah there.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the crowds heard Philip and saw the signs he performed, they all paid close attention to what he said.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>For with shrieks, impure spirits came out of many,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27184I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27184I\"></sup> and many who were paralyzed or lame were healed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27184J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27184J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So there was great joy in that city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now for some time a man named Simon had practiced sorcery<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27186K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27186K\"></sup> in the city and amazed all the people of Samaria. He boasted that he was someone great,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27186L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27186L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and all the people, both high and low, gave him their attention and exclaimed, “This man is rightly called the Great Power of God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27187M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27187M\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They followed him because he had amazed them for a long time with his sorcery.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But when they believed Philip as he proclaimed the good news of the kingdom of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27189N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27189N\"></sup> and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27189O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27189O\"></sup> both men and women.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Simon himself believed and was baptized. And he followed Philip everywhere, astonished by the great signs and miracles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27190P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27190P\"></sup> he saw.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When the apostles in Jerusalem heard that Samaria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27191Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27191Q\"></sup> had accepted the word of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27191R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27191R\"></sup> they sent Peter and John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27191S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27191S\"></sup> to Samaria.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When they arrived, they prayed for the new believers there that they might receive the Holy Spirit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27192T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27192T\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>because the Holy Spirit had not yet come on any of them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27193U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27193U\"></sup> they had simply been baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27193V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27193V\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Peter and John placed their hands on them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27194W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27194W\"></sup> and they received the Holy Spirit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27194X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27194X\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When Simon saw that the Spirit was given at the laying on of the apostles’ hands, he offered them money",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and said, “Give me also this ability so that everyone on whom I lay my hands may receive the Holy Spirit.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Peter answered: “May your money perish with you, because you thought you could buy the gift of God with money!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27197Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27197Y\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You have no part or share<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27198Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27198Z\"></sup> in this ministry, because your heart is not right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27198AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27198AA\"></sup> before God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Repent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27199AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27199AB\"></sup> of this wickedness and pray to the Lord in the hope that he may forgive you for having such a thought in your heart.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For I see that you are full of bitterness and captive to sin.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Simon answered, “Pray to the Lord for me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27201AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27201AC\"></sup> so that nothing you have said may happen to me.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>After they had further proclaimed the word of the Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27202AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27202AD\"></sup> and testified about Jesus, Peter and John returned to Jerusalem, preaching the gospel in many Samaritan villages.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27202AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27202AE\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27203AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27203AF\"></sup> of the Lord said to Philip,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27203AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27203AG\"></sup> “Go south to the road—the desert road—that goes down from Jerusalem to Gaza.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So he started out, and on his way he met an Ethiopian<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27204AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27204AH\"></sup> eunuch,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27204AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27204AI\"></sup> an important official in charge of all the treasury of the Kandake (which means “queen of the Ethiopians”). This man had gone to Jerusalem to worship,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27204AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27204AJ\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and on his way home was sitting in his chariot reading the Book of Isaiah the prophet.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The Spirit told<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27206AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27206AK\"></sup> Philip, “Go to that chariot and stay near it.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Philip ran up to the chariot and heard the man reading Isaiah the prophet. “Do you understand what you are reading?” Philip asked.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“How can I,” he said, “unless someone explains it to me?” So he invited Philip to come up and sit with him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>This is the passage of Scripture the eunuch was reading:“He was led like a sheep to the slaughter,and as a lamb before its shearer is silent,so he did not open his mouth.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In his humiliation he was deprived of justice.Who can speak of his descendants?For his life was taken from the earth.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27210AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27210AL\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The eunuch asked Philip, “Tell me, please, who is the prophet talking about, himself or someone else?”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then Philip began<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27212AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27212AM\"></sup> with that very passage of Scripture<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27212AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27212AN\"></sup> and told him the good news<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27212AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27212AO\"></sup> about Jesus.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>As they traveled along the road, they came to some water and the eunuch said, “Look, here is water. What can stand in the way of my being baptized?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27213AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27213AP\"></sup><sup class=\"versenum\">[37] </sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And he gave orders to stop the chariot. Then both Philip and the eunuch went down into the water and Philip baptized him.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When they came up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord suddenly took Philip away,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27216AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27216AQ\"></sup> and the eunuch did not see him again, but went on his way rejoicing.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Philip, however, appeared at Azotus and traveled about, preaching the gospel in all the towns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27217AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27217AR\"></sup> until he reached Caesarea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27217AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27217AS\"></sup>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Meanwhile, Saul was still breathing out murderous threats against the Lord’s disciples.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27218B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27218B\"></sup> He went to the high priest",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and asked him for letters to the synagogues in Damascus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27219C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27219C\"></sup> so that if he found any there who belonged to the Way,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27219D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27219D\"></sup> whether men or women, he might take them as prisoners to Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>As he neared Damascus on his journey, suddenly a light from heaven flashed around him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27220E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27220E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He fell to the ground and heard a voice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27221F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27221F\"></sup> say to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Saul, Saul, why do you persecute me?”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Who are you, Lord?” Saul asked.<span class=\"woj\">“I am Jesus, whom you are persecuting,”</span> he replied.",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Now get up and go into the city, and you will be told what you must do.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27223G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27223G\"></sup></span>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The men traveling with Saul stood there speechless; they heard the sound<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27224H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27224H\"></sup> but did not see anyone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27224I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27224I\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Saul got up from the ground, but when he opened his eyes he could see nothing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27225J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27225J\"></sup> So they led him by the hand into Damascus.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For three days he was blind, and did not eat or drink anything.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In Damascus there was a disciple named Ananias. The Lord called to him in a vision,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27227K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27227K\"></sup> <span class=\"woj\">“Ananias!”</span>“Yes, Lord,” he answered.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The Lord told him, <span class=\"woj\">“Go to the house of Judas on Straight Street and ask for a man from Tarsus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27228L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27228L\"></sup> named Saul, for he is praying.</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>In a vision he has seen a man named Ananias come and place his hands on<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27229M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27229M\"></sup> him to restore his sight.”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Lord,” Ananias answered, “I have heard many reports about this man and all the harm he has done to your holy people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27230N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27230N\"></sup> in Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27230O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27230O\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he has come here with authority from the chief priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27231P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27231P\"></sup> to arrest all who call on your name.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27231Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27231Q\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But the Lord said to Ananias, <span class=\"woj\">“Go! This man is my chosen instrument<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27232R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27232R\"></sup> to proclaim my name to the Gentiles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27232S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27232S\"></sup> and their kings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27232T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27232T\"></sup> and to the people of Israel.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I will show him how much he must suffer for my name.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27233U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27233U\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Ananias went to the house and entered it. Placing his hands on<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27234V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27234V\"></sup> Saul, he said, “Brother Saul, the Lord—Jesus, who appeared to you on the road as you were coming here—has sent me so that you may see again and be filled with the Holy Spirit.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27234W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27234W\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Immediately, something like scales fell from Saul’s eyes, and he could see again. He got up and was baptized,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27235X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27235X\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and after taking some food, he regained his strength.Saul spent several days with the disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27236Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27236Y\"></sup> in Damascus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27236Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27236Z\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>At once he began to preach in the synagogues<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27237AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27237AA\"></sup> that Jesus is the Son of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27237AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27237AB\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>All those who heard him were astonished and asked, “Isn’t he the man who raised havoc in Jerusalem among those who call on this name?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27238AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27238AC\"></sup> And hasn’t he come here to take them as prisoners to the chief priests?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27238AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27238AD\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Yet Saul grew more and more powerful and baffled the Jews living in Damascus by proving that Jesus is the Messiah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27239AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27239AE\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>After many days had gone by, there was a conspiracy among the Jews to kill him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27240AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27240AF\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>but Saul learned of their plan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27241AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27241AG\"></sup> Day and night they kept close watch on the city gates in order to kill him.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But his followers took him by night and lowered him in a basket through an opening in the wall.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27242AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27242AH\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When he came to Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27243AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27243AI\"></sup> he tried to join the disciples, but they were all afraid of him, not believing that he really was a disciple.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Barnabas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27244AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27244AJ\"></sup> took him and brought him to the apostles. He told them how Saul on his journey had seen the Lord and that the Lord had spoken to him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27244AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27244AK\"></sup> and how in Damascus he had preached fearlessly in the name of Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27244AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27244AL\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Saul stayed with them and moved about freely in Jerusalem, speaking boldly in the name of the Lord.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He talked and debated with the Hellenistic Jews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27246AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27246AM\"></sup> but they tried to kill him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27246AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27246AN\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When the believers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27247AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27247AO\"></sup> learned of this, they took him down to Caesarea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27247AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27247AP\"></sup> and sent him off to Tarsus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27247AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27247AQ\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then the church throughout Judea, Galilee and Samaria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27248AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27248AR\"></sup> enjoyed a time of peace and was strengthened. Living in the fear of the Lord and encouraged by the Holy Spirit, it increased in numbers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27248AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27248AS\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>As Peter traveled about the country, he went to visit the Lord’s people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27249AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27249AT\"></sup> who lived in Lydda.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>There he found a man named Aeneas, who was paralyzed and had been bedridden for eight years.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Aeneas,” Peter said to him, “Jesus Christ heals you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27251AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27251AU\"></sup> Get up and roll up your mat.” Immediately Aeneas got up.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>All those who lived in Lydda and Sharon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27252AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27252AV\"></sup> saw him and turned to the Lord.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27252AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27252AW\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>In Joppa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27253AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27253AX\"></sup> there was a disciple named Tabitha (in Greek her name is Dorcas); she was always doing good<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27253AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27253AY\"></sup> and helping the poor.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>About that time she became sick and died, and her body was washed and placed in an upstairs room.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27254AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27254AZ\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Lydda was near Joppa; so when the disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27255BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27255BA\"></sup> heard that Peter was in Lydda, they sent two men to him and urged him, “Please come at once!”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Peter went with them, and when he arrived he was taken upstairs to the room. All the widows<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27256BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27256BB\"></sup> stood around him, crying and showing him the robes and other clothing that Dorcas had made while she was still with them.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Peter sent them all out of the room;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27257BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27257BC\"></sup> then he got down on his knees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27257BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27257BD\"></sup> and prayed. Turning toward the dead woman, he said, “Tabitha, get up.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27257BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27257BE\"></sup> She opened her eyes, and seeing Peter she sat up.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He took her by the hand and helped her to her feet. Then he called for the believers, especially the widows, and presented her to them alive.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>This became known all over Joppa, and many people believed in the Lord.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27259BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27259BF\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Peter stayed in Joppa for some time with a tanner named Simon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27260BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27260BG\"></sup>"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>At Caesarea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27261A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27261A\"></sup> there was a man named Cornelius, a centurion in what was known as the Italian Regiment.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He and all his family were devout and God-fearing;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27262B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27262B\"></sup> he gave generously to those in need and prayed to God regularly.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>One day at about three in the afternoon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27263C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27263C\"></sup> he had a vision.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27263D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27263D\"></sup> He distinctly saw an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27263E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27263E\"></sup> of God, who came to him and said, “Cornelius!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Cornelius stared at him in fear. “What is it, Lord?” he asked.The angel answered, “Your prayers and gifts to the poor have come up as a memorial offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27264F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27264F\"></sup> before God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27264G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27264G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now send men to Joppa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27265H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27265H\"></sup> to bring back a man named Simon who is called Peter.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He is staying with Simon the tanner,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27266I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27266I\"></sup> whose house is by the sea.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the angel who spoke to him had gone, Cornelius called two of his servants and a devout soldier who was one of his attendants.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He told them everything that had happened and sent them to Joppa.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27268J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27268J\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>About noon the following day as they were on their journey and approaching the city, Peter went up on the roof<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27269L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27269L\"></sup> to pray.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He became hungry and wanted something to eat, and while the meal was being prepared, he fell into a trance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27270M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27270M\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He saw heaven opened<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27271N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27271N\"></sup> and something like a large sheet being let down to earth by its four corners.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>It contained all kinds of four-footed animals, as well as reptiles and birds.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then a voice told him, <span class=\"woj\">“Get up, Peter. Kill and eat.”</span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Surely not, Lord!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27274O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27274O\"></sup> Peter replied. “I have never eaten anything impure or unclean.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27274P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27274P\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The voice spoke to him a second time, <span class=\"woj\">“Do not call anything impure that God has made clean.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27275Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27275Q\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>This happened three times, and immediately the sheet was taken back to heaven.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>While Peter was wondering about the meaning of the vision,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27277R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27277R\"></sup> the men sent by Cornelius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27277S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27277S\"></sup> found out where Simon’s house was and stopped at the gate.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They called out, asking if Simon who was known as Peter was staying there.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>While Peter was still thinking about the vision,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27279T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27279T\"></sup> the Spirit said<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27279U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27279U\"></sup> to him, “Simon, three men are looking for you.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So get up and go downstairs. Do not hesitate to go with them, for I have sent them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27280V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27280V\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Peter went down and said to the men, “I’m the one you’re looking for. Why have you come?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The men replied, “We have come from Cornelius the centurion. He is a righteous and God-fearing man,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27282W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27282W\"></sup> who is respected by all the Jewish people. A holy angel told him to ask you to come to his house so that he could hear what you have to say.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27282X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27282X\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Peter invited the men into the house to be his guests.The next day Peter started out with them, and some of the believers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27283Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27283Y\"></sup> from Joppa went along.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27283Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27283Z\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The following day he arrived in Caesarea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27284AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27284AA\"></sup> Cornelius was expecting them and had called together his relatives and close friends.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As Peter entered the house, Cornelius met him and fell at his feet in reverence.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Peter made him get up. “Stand up,” he said, “I am only a man myself.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27286AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27286AB\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>While talking with him, Peter went inside and found a large gathering of people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27287AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27287AC\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He said to them: “You are well aware that it is against our law for a Jew to associate with or visit a Gentile.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27288AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27288AD\"></sup> But God has shown me that I should not call anyone impure or unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27288AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27288AE\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So when I was sent for, I came without raising any objection. May I ask why you sent for me?”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Cornelius answered: “Three days ago I was in my house praying at this hour, at three in the afternoon. Suddenly a man in shining clothes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27290AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27290AF\"></sup> stood before me",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and said, ‘Cornelius, God has heard your prayer and remembered your gifts to the poor.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Send to Joppa for Simon who is called Peter. He is a guest in the home of Simon the tanner, who lives by the sea.’",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So I sent for you immediately, and it was good of you to come. Now we are all here in the presence of God to listen to everything the Lord has commanded you to tell us.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Peter began to speak: “I now realize how true it is that God does not show favoritism<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27294AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27294AG\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>but accepts from every nation the one who fears him and does what is right.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27295AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27295AH\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>You know the message<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27296AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27296AI\"></sup> God sent to the people of Israel, announcing the good news<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27296AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27296AJ\"></sup> of peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27296AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27296AK\"></sup> through Jesus Christ, who is Lord of all.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27296AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27296AL\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>You know what has happened throughout the province of Judea, beginning in Galilee after the baptism that John preached—",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>how God anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27298AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27298AM\"></sup> Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Spirit and power, and how he went around doing good and healing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27298AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27298AN\"></sup> all who were under the power of the devil, because God was with him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27298AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27298AO\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“We are witnesses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27299AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27299AP\"></sup> of everything he did in the country of the Jews and in Jerusalem. They killed him by hanging him on a cross,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27299AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27299AQ\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>but God raised him from the dead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27300AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27300AR\"></sup> on the third day and caused him to be seen.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He was not seen by all the people,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27301AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27301AS\"></sup> but by witnesses whom God had already chosen—by us who ate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27301AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27301AT\"></sup> and drank with him after he rose from the dead.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>He commanded us to preach to the people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27302AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27302AU\"></sup> and to testify that he is the one whom God appointed as judge of the living and the dead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27302AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27302AV\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>All the prophets testify about him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27303AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27303AW\"></sup> that everyone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27303AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27303AX\"></sup> who believes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27303AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27303AY\"></sup> in him receives forgiveness of sins through his name.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27303AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27303AZ\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>While Peter was still speaking these words, the Holy Spirit came on<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27304BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27304BA\"></sup> all who heard the message.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>The circumcised believers who had come with Peter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27305BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27305BB\"></sup> were astonished that the gift of the Holy Spirit had been poured out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27305BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27305BC\"></sup> even on Gentiles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27305BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27305BD\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>For they heard them speaking in tongues<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27306BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27306BE\"></sup> and praising God.Then Peter said,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“Surely no one can stand in the way of their being baptized with water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27307BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27307BF\"></sup> They have received the Holy Spirit just as we have.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27307BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27307BG\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>So he ordered that they be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27308BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27308BH\"></sup> Then they asked Peter to stay with them for a few days."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>The apostles and the believers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27309A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27309A\"></sup> throughout Judea heard that the Gentiles also had received the word of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27309B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27309B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So when Peter went up to Jerusalem, the circumcised believers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27310C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27310C\"></sup> criticized him",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and said, “You went into the house of uncircumcised men and ate with them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27311D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27311D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Starting from the beginning, Peter told them the whole story:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“I was in the city of Joppa praying, and in a trance I saw a vision.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27313E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27313E\"></sup> I saw something like a large sheet being let down from heaven by its four corners, and it came down to where I was.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I looked into it and saw four-footed animals of the earth, wild beasts, reptiles and birds.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then I heard a voice telling me, <span class=\"woj\">‘Get up, Peter. Kill and eat.’</span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“I replied, ‘Surely not, Lord! Nothing impure or unclean has ever entered my mouth.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“The voice spoke from heaven a second time, <span class=\"woj\">‘Do not call anything impure that God has made clean.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27317F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27317F\"></sup></span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>This happened three times, and then it was all pulled up to heaven again.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Right then three men who had been sent to me from Caesarea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27319G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27319G\"></sup> stopped at the house where I was staying.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The Spirit told<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27320H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27320H\"></sup> me to have no hesitation about going with them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27320I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27320I\"></sup> These six brothers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27320J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27320J\"></sup> also went with me, and we entered the man’s house.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He told us how he had seen an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27321K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27321K\"></sup> appear in his house and say, ‘Send to Joppa for Simon who is called Peter.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He will bring you a message<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27322L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27322L\"></sup> through which you and all your household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27322M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27322M\"></sup> will be saved.’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“As I began to speak, the Holy Spirit came on<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27323N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27323N\"></sup> them as he had come on us at the beginning.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27323O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27323O\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then I remembered what the Lord had said: <span class=\"woj\">‘John baptized with water,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27324P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27324P\"></sup> but you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27324Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27324Q\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So if God gave them the same gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27325R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27325R\"></sup> he gave us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27325S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27325S\"></sup> who believed in the Lord Jesus Christ, who was I to think that I could stand in God’s way?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When they heard this, they had no further objections and praised God, saying, “So then, even to Gentiles God has granted repentance that leads to life.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27326T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27326T\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now those who had been scattered by the persecution that broke out when Stephen was killed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27327U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27327U\"></sup> traveled as far as Phoenicia, Cyprus and Antioch,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27327V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27327V\"></sup> spreading the word only among Jews.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Some of them, however, men from Cyprus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27328W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27328W\"></sup> and Cyrene,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27328X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27328X\"></sup> went to Antioch<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27328Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27328Y\"></sup> and began to speak to Greeks also, telling them the good news<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27328Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27328Z\"></sup> about the Lord Jesus.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The Lord’s hand was with them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27329AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27329AA\"></sup> and a great number of people believed and turned to the Lord.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27329AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27329AB\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>News of this reached the church in Jerusalem, and they sent Barnabas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27330AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27330AC\"></sup> to Antioch.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When he arrived and saw what the grace of God had done,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27331AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27331AD\"></sup> he was glad and encouraged them all to remain true to the Lord with all their hearts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27331AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27331AE\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He was a good man, full of the Holy Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27332AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27332AF\"></sup> and faith, and a great number of people were brought to the Lord.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27332AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27332AG\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Barnabas went to Tarsus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27333AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27333AH\"></sup> to look for Saul,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and when he found him, he brought him to Antioch. So for a whole year Barnabas and Saul met with the church and taught great numbers of people. The disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27334AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27334AI\"></sup> were called Christians first<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27334AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27334AJ\"></sup> at Antioch.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>During this time some prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27335AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27335AK\"></sup> came down from Jerusalem to Antioch.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>One of them, named Agabus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27336AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27336AL\"></sup> stood up and through the Spirit predicted that a severe famine would spread over the entire Roman world.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27336AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27336AM\"></sup> (This happened during the reign of Claudius.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27336AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27336AN\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The disciples,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27337AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27337AO\"></sup> as each one was able, decided to provide help<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27337AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27337AP\"></sup> for the brothers and sisters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27337AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27337AQ\"></sup> living in Judea.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>This they did, sending their gift to the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27338AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27338AR\"></sup> by Barnabas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27338AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27338AS\"></sup> and Saul.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27338AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27338AT\"></sup>"
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>It was about this time that King Herod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27339A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27339A\"></sup> arrested some who belonged to the church, intending to persecute them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He had James, the brother of John,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27340B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27340B\"></sup> put to death with the sword.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27340C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27340C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When he saw that this met with approval among the Jews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27341D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27341D\"></sup> he proceeded to seize Peter also. This happened during the Festival of Unleavened Bread.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27341E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27341E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>After arresting him, he put him in prison, handing him over to be guarded by four squads of four soldiers each. Herod intended to bring him out for public trial after the Passover.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27342F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27342F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So Peter was kept in prison, but the church was earnestly praying to God for him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27343G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27343G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The night before Herod was to bring him to trial, Peter was sleeping between two soldiers, bound with two chains,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27344H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27344H\"></sup> and sentries stood guard at the entrance.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Suddenly an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27345I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27345I\"></sup> of the Lord appeared and a light shone in the cell. He struck Peter on the side and woke him up. “Quick, get up!” he said, and the chains fell off Peter’s wrists.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27345J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27345J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the angel said to him, “Put on your clothes and sandals.” And Peter did so. “Wrap your cloak around you and follow me,” the angel told him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Peter followed him out of the prison, but he had no idea that what the angel was doing was really happening; he thought he was seeing a vision.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27347K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27347K\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They passed the first and second guards and came to the iron gate leading to the city. It opened for them by itself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27348L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27348L\"></sup> and they went through it. When they had walked the length of one street, suddenly the angel left him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Peter came to himself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27349M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27349M\"></sup> and said, “Now I know without a doubt that the Lord has sent his angel and rescued me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27349N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27349N\"></sup> from Herod’s clutches and from everything the Jewish people were hoping would happen.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When this had dawned on him, he went to the house of Mary the mother of John, also called Mark,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27350O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27350O\"></sup> where many people had gathered and were praying.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27350P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27350P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Peter knocked at the outer entrance, and a servant named Rhoda came to answer the door.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27351Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27351Q\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When she recognized Peter’s voice, she was so overjoyed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27352R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27352R\"></sup> she ran back without opening it and exclaimed, “Peter is at the door!”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“You’re out of your mind,” they told her. When she kept insisting that it was so, they said, “It must be his angel.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27353S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27353S\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But Peter kept on knocking, and when they opened the door and saw him, they were astonished.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Peter motioned with his hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27355T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27355T\"></sup> for them to be quiet and described how the Lord had brought him out of prison. “Tell James<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27355U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27355U\"></sup> and the other brothers and sisters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27355V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27355V\"></sup> about this,” he said, and then he left for another place.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>In the morning, there was no small commotion among the soldiers as to what had become of Peter.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>After Herod had a thorough search made for him and did not find him, he cross-examined the guards and ordered that they be executed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27357W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27357W\"></sup>Then Herod went from Judea to Caesarea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27357X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27357X\"></sup> and stayed there.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He had been quarreling with the people of Tyre and Sidon;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27358Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27358Y\"></sup> they now joined together and sought an audience with him. After securing the support of Blastus, a trusted personal servant of the king, they asked for peace, because they depended on the king’s country for their food supply.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27358Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27358Z\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>On the appointed day Herod, wearing his royal robes, sat on his throne and delivered a public address to the people.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>They shouted, “This is the voice of a god, not of a man.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Immediately, because Herod did not give praise to God, an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27361AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27361AA\"></sup> of the Lord struck him down,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27361AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27361AB\"></sup> and he was eaten by worms and died.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But the word of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27362AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27362AC\"></sup> continued to spread and flourish.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27362AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27362AD\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When Barnabas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27363AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27363AE\"></sup> and Saul had finished their mission,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27363AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27363AF\"></sup> they returned from Jerusalem, taking with them John, also called Mark.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27363AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27363AG\"></sup>"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum mid-paragraph\">13 </span><sup class=\"versenum mid-paragraph\">1 </sup>Now in the church at Antioch<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27364A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27364A\"></sup> there were prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27364B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27364B\"></sup> and teachers:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27364C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27364C\"></sup> Barnabas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27364D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27364D\"></sup> Simeon called Niger, Lucius of Cyrene,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27364E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27364E\"></sup> Manaen (who had been brought up with Herod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27364F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27364F\"></sup> the tetrarch) and Saul.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>While they were worshiping the Lord and fasting, the Holy Spirit said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27365G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27365G\"></sup> “Set apart for me Barnabas and Saul for the work<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27365H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27365H\"></sup> to which I have called them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27365I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27365I\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So after they had fasted and prayed, they placed their hands on them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27366J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27366J\"></sup> and sent them off.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27366K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27366K\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The two of them, sent on their way by the Holy Spirit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27367L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27367L\"></sup> went down to Seleucia and sailed from there to Cyprus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27367M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27367M\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When they arrived at Salamis, they proclaimed the word of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27368N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27368N\"></sup> in the Jewish synagogues.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27368O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27368O\"></sup> John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27368P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27368P\"></sup> was with them as their helper.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They traveled through the whole island until they came to Paphos. There they met a Jewish sorcerer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27369Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27369Q\"></sup> and false prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27369R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27369R\"></sup> named Bar-Jesus,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>who was an attendant of the proconsul,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27370S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27370S\"></sup> Sergius Paulus. The proconsul, an intelligent man, sent for Barnabas and Saul because he wanted to hear the word of God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Elymas the sorcerer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27371T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27371T\"></sup> (for that is what his name means) opposed them and tried to turn the proconsul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27371U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27371U\"></sup> from the faith.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27371V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27371V\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Saul, who was also called Paul, filled with the Holy Spirit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27372W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27372W\"></sup> looked straight at Elymas and said,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“You are a child of the devil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27373X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27373X\"></sup> and an enemy of everything that is right! You are full of all kinds of deceit and trickery. Will you never stop perverting the right ways of the Lord?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27373Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27373Y\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the hand of the Lord is against you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27374Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27374Z\"></sup> You are going to be blind for a time, not even able to see the light of the sun.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27374AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27374AA\"></sup>Immediately mist and darkness came over him, and he groped about, seeking someone to lead him by the hand.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the proconsul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27375AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27375AB\"></sup> saw what had happened, he believed, for he was amazed at the teaching about the Lord.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>From Paphos,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27376AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27376AC\"></sup> Paul and his companions sailed to Perga in Pamphylia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27376AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27376AD\"></sup> where John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27376AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27376AE\"></sup> left them to return to Jerusalem.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>From Perga they went on to Pisidian Antioch.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27377AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27377AF\"></sup> On the Sabbath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27377AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27377AG\"></sup> they entered the synagogue<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27377AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27377AH\"></sup> and sat down.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>After the reading from the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27378AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27378AI\"></sup> and the Prophets, the leaders of the synagogue sent word to them, saying, “Brothers, if you have a word of exhortation for the people, please speak.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Standing up, Paul motioned with his hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27379AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27379AJ\"></sup> and said: “Fellow Israelites and you Gentiles who worship God, listen to me!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The God of the people of Israel chose our ancestors; he made the people prosper during their stay in Egypt; with mighty power he led them out of that country;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27380AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27380AK\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>for about forty years he endured their conduct<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27381AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27381AL\"></sup> in the wilderness;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27381AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27381AM\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and he overthrew seven nations in Canaan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27382AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27382AN\"></sup> giving their land to his people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27382AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27382AO\"></sup> as their inheritance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27382AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27382AP\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All this took about 450 years.“After this, God gave them judges<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27383AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27383AQ\"></sup> until the time of Samuel the prophet.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27383AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27383AR\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the people asked for a king,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27384AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27384AS\"></sup> and he gave them Saul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27384AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27384AT\"></sup> son of Kish, of the tribe of Benjamin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27384AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27384AU\"></sup> who ruled forty years.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>After removing Saul,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27385AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27385AV\"></sup> he made David their king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27385AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27385AW\"></sup> God testified concerning him: ‘I have found David son of Jesse, a man after my own heart;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27385AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27385AX\"></sup> he will do everything I want him to do.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27385AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27385AY\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“From this man’s descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27386AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27386AZ\"></sup> God has brought to Israel the Savior<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27386BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27386BA\"></sup> Jesus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27386BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27386BB\"></sup> as he promised.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27386BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27386BC\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Before the coming of Jesus, John preached repentance and baptism to all the people of Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27387BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27387BD\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As John was completing his work,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27388BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27388BE\"></sup> he said: ‘Who do you suppose I am? I am not the one you are looking for.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27388BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27388BF\"></sup> But there is one coming after me whose sandals I am not worthy to untie.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27388BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27388BG\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Fellow children of Abraham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27389BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27389BH\"></sup> and you God-fearing Gentiles, it is to us that this message of salvation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27389BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27389BI\"></sup> has been sent.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The people of Jerusalem and their rulers did not recognize Jesus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27390BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27390BJ\"></sup> yet in condemning him they fulfilled the words of the prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27390BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27390BK\"></sup> that are read every Sabbath.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Though they found no proper ground for a death sentence, they asked Pilate to have him executed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27391BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27391BL\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When they had carried out all that was written about him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27392BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27392BM\"></sup> they took him down from the cross<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27392BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27392BN\"></sup> and laid him in a tomb.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27392BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27392BO\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But God raised him from the dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27393BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27393BP\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and for many days he was seen by those who had traveled with him from Galilee to Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27394BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27394BQ\"></sup> They are now his witnesses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27394BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27394BR\"></sup> to our people.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“We tell you the good news:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27395BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27395BS\"></sup> What God promised our ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27395BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27395BT\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>he has fulfilled for us, their children, by raising up Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27396BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27396BU\"></sup> As it is written in the second Psalm:“‘You are my son;today I have become your father.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27396BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27396BV\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>God raised him from the dead so that he will never be subject to decay. As God has said,“‘I will give you the holy and sure blessings promised to David.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27397BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27397BW\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So it is also stated elsewhere:“‘You will not let your holy one see decay.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27398BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27398BX\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“Now when David had served God’s purpose in his own generation, he fell asleep;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27399BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27399BY\"></sup> he was buried with his ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27399BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27399BZ\"></sup> and his body decayed.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But the one whom God raised from the dead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27400CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27400CA\"></sup> did not see decay.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“Therefore, my friends, I want you to know that through Jesus the forgiveness of sins is proclaimed to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27401CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27401CB\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Through him everyone who believes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27402CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27402CC\"></sup> is set free from every sin, a justification you were not able to obtain under the law of Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27402CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27402CD\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Take care that what the prophets have said does not happen to you:",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“‘Look, you scoffers,wonder and perish,for I am going to do something in your daysthat you would never believe,even if someone told you.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27404CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27404CE\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>As Paul and Barnabas were leaving the synagogue,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27405CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27405CF\"></sup> the people invited them to speak further about these things on the next Sabbath.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>When the congregation was dismissed, many of the Jews and devout converts to Judaism followed Paul and Barnabas, who talked with them and urged them to continue in the grace of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27406CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27406CG\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>On the next Sabbath almost the whole city gathered to hear the word of the Lord.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When the Jews saw the crowds, they were filled with jealousy. They began to contradict what Paul was saying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27408CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27408CH\"></sup> and heaped abuse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27408CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27408CI\"></sup> on him.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then Paul and Barnabas answered them boldly: “We had to speak the word of God to you first.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27409CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27409CJ\"></sup> Since you reject it and do not consider yourselves worthy of eternal life, we now turn to the Gentiles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27409CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27409CK\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>For this is what the Lord has commanded us:“‘I have made you a light for the Gentiles,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27410CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27410CL\"></sup>that you may bring salvation to the ends of the earth.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27410CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27410CM\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>When the Gentiles heard this, they were glad and honored the word of the Lord;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27411CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27411CN\"></sup> and all who were appointed for eternal life believed.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>The word of the Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27412CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27412CO\"></sup> spread through the whole region.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>But the Jewish leaders incited the God-fearing women of high standing and the leading men of the city. They stirred up persecution against Paul and Barnabas, and expelled them from their region.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27413CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27413CP\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>So they shook the dust off their feet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27414CQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CQ&quot;&gt;CQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27414CQ\"></sup> as a warning to them and went to Iconium.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27414CR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CR&quot;&gt;CR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27414CR\"></sup>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>And the disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27415CS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CS&quot;&gt;CS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27415CS\"></sup> were filled with joy and with the Holy Spirit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27415CT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CT&quot;&gt;CT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27415CT\"></sup>"
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>At Iconium<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27416A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27416A\"></sup> Paul and Barnabas went as usual into the Jewish synagogue.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27416B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27416B\"></sup> There they spoke so effectively that a great number<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27416C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27416C\"></sup> of Jews and Greeks believed.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But the Jews who refused to believe stirred up the other Gentiles and poisoned their minds against the brothers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27417D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27417D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Paul and Barnabas spent considerable time there, speaking boldly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27418E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27418E\"></sup> for the Lord, who confirmed the message of his grace by enabling them to perform signs and wonders.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27418F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27418F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The people of the city were divided; some sided with the Jews, others with the apostles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27419G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27419G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>There was a plot afoot among both Gentiles and Jews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27420H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27420H\"></sup> together with their leaders, to mistreat them and stone them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27420I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27420I\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But they found out about it and fled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27421J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27421J\"></sup> to the Lycaonian cities of Lystra and Derbe and to the surrounding country,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>where they continued to preach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27422K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27422K\"></sup> the gospel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27422L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27422L\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In Lystra there sat a man who was lame. He had been that way from birth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27423M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27423M\"></sup> and had never walked.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He listened to Paul as he was speaking. Paul looked directly at him, saw that he had faith to be healed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27424N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27424N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and called out, “Stand up on your feet!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27425O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27425O\"></sup> At that, the man jumped up and began to walk.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27425P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27425P\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the crowd saw what Paul had done, they shouted in the Lycaonian language, “The gods have come down to us in human form!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27426Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27426Q\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Barnabas they called Zeus, and Paul they called Hermes because he was the chief speaker.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27427R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27427R\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The priest of Zeus, whose temple was just outside the city, brought bulls and wreaths to the city gates because he and the crowd wanted to offer sacrifices to them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But when the apostles Barnabas and Paul heard of this, they tore their clothes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27429S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27429S\"></sup> and rushed out into the crowd, shouting:",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Friends, why are you doing this? We too are only human,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27430T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27430T\"></sup> like you. We are bringing you good news,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27430U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27430U\"></sup> telling you to turn from these worthless things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27430V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27430V\"></sup> to the living God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27430W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27430W\"></sup> who made the heavens and the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27430X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27430X\"></sup> and the sea and everything in them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27430Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27430Y\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>In the past, he let<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27431Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27431Z\"></sup> all nations go their own way.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27431AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27431AA\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Yet he has not left himself without testimony:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27432AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27432AB\"></sup> He has shown kindness by giving you rain from heaven and crops in their seasons;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27432AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27432AC\"></sup> he provides you with plenty of food and fills your hearts with joy.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27432AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27432AD\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Even with these words, they had difficulty keeping the crowd from sacrificing to them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then some Jews<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27434AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27434AE\"></sup> came from Antioch and Iconium<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27434AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27434AF\"></sup> and won the crowd over. They stoned Paul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27434AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27434AG\"></sup> and dragged him outside the city, thinking he was dead.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But after the disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27435AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27435AH\"></sup> had gathered around him, he got up and went back into the city. The next day he and Barnabas left for Derbe.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They preached the gospel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27436AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27436AI\"></sup> in that city and won a large number<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27436AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27436AJ\"></sup> of disciples. Then they returned to Lystra, Iconium<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27436AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27436AK\"></sup> and Antioch,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>strengthening the disciples and encouraging them to remain true to the faith.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27437AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27437AL\"></sup> “We must go through many hardships<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27437AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27437AM\"></sup> to enter the kingdom of God,” they said.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Paul and Barnabas appointed elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27438AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27438AN\"></sup> for them in each church and, with prayer and fasting,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27438AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27438AO\"></sup> committed them to the Lord,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27438AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27438AP\"></sup> in whom they had put their trust.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After going through Pisidia, they came into Pamphylia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27439AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27439AQ\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and when they had preached the word in Perga, they went down to Attalia.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>From Attalia they sailed back to Antioch,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27441AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27441AR\"></sup> where they had been committed to the grace of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27441AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27441AS\"></sup> for the work they had now completed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27441AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27441AT\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>On arriving there, they gathered the church together and reported all that God had done through them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27442AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27442AU\"></sup> and how he had opened a door<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27442AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27442AV\"></sup> of faith to the Gentiles.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And they stayed there a long time with the disciples.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27443AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27443AW\"></sup>"
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>Certain people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27444A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27444A\"></sup> came down from Judea to Antioch and were teaching the believers:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27444B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27444B\"></sup> “Unless you are circumcised,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27444C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27444C\"></sup> according to the custom taught by Moses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27444D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27444D\"></sup> you cannot be saved.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>This brought Paul and Barnabas into sharp dispute and debate with them. So Paul and Barnabas were appointed, along with some other believers, to go up to Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27445E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27445E\"></sup> to see the apostles and elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27445F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27445F\"></sup> about this question.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The church sent them on their way, and as they traveled through Phoenicia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27446G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27446G\"></sup> and Samaria, they told how the Gentiles had been converted.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27446H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27446H\"></sup> This news made all the believers very glad.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When they came to Jerusalem, they were welcomed by the church and the apostles and elders, to whom they reported everything God had done through them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27447I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27447I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then some of the believers who belonged to the party<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27448J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27448J\"></sup> of the Pharisees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27448K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27448K\"></sup> stood up and said, “The Gentiles must be circumcised and required to keep the law of Moses.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27448L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27448L\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The apostles and elders met to consider this question.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>After much discussion, Peter got up and addressed them: “Brothers, you know that some time ago God made a choice among you that the Gentiles might hear from my lips the message of the gospel and believe.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27450M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27450M\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>God, who knows the heart,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27451N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27451N\"></sup> showed that he accepted them by giving the Holy Spirit to them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27451O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27451O\"></sup> just as he did to us.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He did not discriminate between us and them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27452P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27452P\"></sup> for he purified their hearts by faith.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27452Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27452Q\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now then, why do you try to test God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27453R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27453R\"></sup> by putting on the necks of Gentiles a yoke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27453S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27453S\"></sup> that neither we nor our ancestors have been able to bear?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>No! We believe it is through the grace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27454T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27454T\"></sup> of our Lord Jesus that we are saved, just as they are.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The whole assembly became silent as they listened to Barnabas and Paul telling about the signs and wonders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27455U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27455U\"></sup> God had done among the Gentiles through them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27455V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27455V\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When they finished, James<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27456W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27456W\"></sup> spoke up. “Brothers,” he said, “listen to me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Simon has described to us how God first intervened to choose a people for his name from the Gentiles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27457X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27457X\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The words of the prophets are in agreement with this, as it is written:",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“‘After this I will returnand rebuild David’s fallen tent.Its ruins I will rebuild,and I will restore it,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>that the rest of mankind may seek the Lord,even all the Gentiles who bear my name,says the Lord, who does these things’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27460Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27460Y\"></sup>—",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>things known from long ago.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27461Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27461Z\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“It is my judgment, therefore, that we should not make it difficult for the Gentiles who are turning to God.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Instead we should write to them, telling them to abstain from food polluted by idols,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27463AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27463AA\"></sup> from sexual immorality,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27463AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27463AB\"></sup> from the meat of strangled animals and from blood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27463AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27463AC\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For the law of Moses has been preached in every city from the earliest times and is read in the synagogues on every Sabbath.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27464AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27464AD\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the apostles and elders,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27465AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27465AE\"></sup> with the whole church, decided to choose some of their own men and send them to Antioch<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27465AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27465AF\"></sup> with Paul and Barnabas. They chose Judas (called Barsabbas) and Silas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27465AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27465AG\"></sup> men who were leaders among the believers.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>With them they sent the following letter:The apostles and elders, your brothers,To the Gentile believers in Antioch,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27466AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27466AH\"></sup> Syria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27466AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27466AI\"></sup> and Cilicia:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27466AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27466AJ\"></sup>Greetings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27466AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27466AK\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>We have heard that some went out from us without our authorization and disturbed you, troubling your minds by what they said.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27467AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27467AL\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So we all agreed to choose some men and send them to you with our dear friends Barnabas and Paul—",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>men who have risked their lives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27469AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27469AM\"></sup> for the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Therefore we are sending Judas and Silas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27470AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27470AN\"></sup> to confirm by word of mouth what we are writing.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>It seemed good to the Holy Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27471AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27471AO\"></sup> and to us not to burden you with anything beyond the following requirements:",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>You are to abstain from food sacrificed to idols, from blood, from the meat of strangled animals and from sexual immorality.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27472AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27472AP\"></sup> You will do well to avoid these things.Farewell.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So the men were sent off and went down to Antioch, where they gathered the church together and delivered the letter.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The people read it and were glad for its encouraging message.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Judas and Silas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27475AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27475AQ\"></sup> who themselves were prophets,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27475AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27475AR\"></sup> said much to encourage and strengthen the believers.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>After spending some time there, they were sent off by the believers with the blessing of peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27476AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27476AS\"></sup> to return to those who had sent them.<sup class=\"versenum\">[34] </sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But Paul and Barnabas remained in Antioch, where they and many others taught and preached<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27478AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27478AT\"></sup> the word of the Lord.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27478AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27478AU\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Some time later Paul said to Barnabas, “Let us go back and visit the believers in all the towns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27479AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27479AV\"></sup> where we preached the word of the Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27479AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27479AW\"></sup> and see how they are doing.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Barnabas wanted to take John, also called Mark,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27480AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27480AX\"></sup> with them,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>but Paul did not think it wise to take him, because he had deserted them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27481AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27481AY\"></sup> in Pamphylia and had not continued with them in the work.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>They had such a sharp disagreement that they parted company. Barnabas took Mark and sailed for Cyprus,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>but Paul chose Silas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27483AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27483AZ\"></sup> and left, commended by the believers to the grace of the Lord.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27483BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27483BA\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He went through Syria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27484BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27484BB\"></sup> and Cilicia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27484BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27484BC\"></sup> strengthening the churches.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27484BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27484BD\"></sup>"
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Paul came to Derbe and then to Lystra,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27485A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27485A\"></sup> where a disciple named Timothy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27485B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27485B\"></sup> lived, whose mother was Jewish and a believer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27485C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27485C\"></sup> but whose father was a Greek.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The believers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27486D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27486D\"></sup> at Lystra and Iconium<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27486E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27486E\"></sup> spoke well of him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Paul wanted to take him along on the journey, so he circumcised him because of the Jews who lived in that area, for they all knew that his father was a Greek.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27487F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27487F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>As they traveled from town to town, they delivered the decisions reached by the apostles and elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27488G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27488G\"></sup> in Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27488H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27488H\"></sup> for the people to obey.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27488I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27488I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the churches were strengthened<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27489J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27489J\"></sup> in the faith and grew daily in numbers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27489K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27489K\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Paul and his companions traveled throughout the region of Phrygia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27490L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27490L\"></sup> and Galatia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27490M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27490M\"></sup> having been kept by the Holy Spirit from preaching the word in the province of Asia.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27490N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27490N\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When they came to the border of Mysia, they tried to enter Bithynia, but the Spirit of Jesus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27491O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27491O\"></sup> would not allow them to.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So they passed by Mysia and went down to Troas.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27492P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27492P\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>During the night Paul had a vision<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27493Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27493Q\"></sup> of a man of Macedonia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27493R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27493R\"></sup> standing and begging him, “Come over to Macedonia and help us.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>After Paul had seen the vision, we<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27494S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27494S\"></sup> got ready at once to leave for Macedonia, concluding that God had called us to preach the gospel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27494T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27494T\"></sup> to them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>From Troas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27495U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27495U\"></sup> we put out to sea and sailed straight for Samothrace, and the next day we went on to Neapolis.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>From there we traveled to Philippi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27496V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27496V\"></sup> a Roman colony and the leading city of that district of Macedonia.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27496W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27496W\"></sup> And we stayed there several days.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>On the Sabbath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27497X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27497X\"></sup> we went outside the city gate to the river, where we expected to find a place of prayer. We sat down and began to speak to the women who had gathered there.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>One of those listening was a woman from the city of Thyatira<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27498Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27498Y\"></sup> named Lydia, a dealer in purple cloth. She was a worshiper of God. The Lord opened her heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27498Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27498Z\"></sup> to respond to Paul’s message.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When she and the members of her household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27499AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27499AA\"></sup> were baptized,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27499AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27499AB\"></sup> she invited us to her home. “If you consider me a believer in the Lord,” she said, “come and stay at my house.” And she persuaded us.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Once when we were going to the place of prayer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27500AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27500AC\"></sup> we were met by a female slave who had a spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27500AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27500AD\"></sup> by which she predicted the future. She earned a great deal of money for her owners by fortune-telling.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>She followed Paul and the rest of us, shouting, “These men are servants of the Most High God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27501AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27501AE\"></sup> who are telling you the way to be saved.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>She kept this up for many days. Finally Paul became so annoyed that he turned around and said to the spirit, “In the name of Jesus Christ I command you to come out of her!” At that moment the spirit left her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27502AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27502AF\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When her owners realized that their hope of making money<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27503AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27503AG\"></sup> was gone, they seized Paul and Silas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27503AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27503AH\"></sup> and dragged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27503AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27503AI\"></sup> them into the marketplace to face the authorities.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They brought them before the magistrates and said, “These men are Jews, and are throwing our city into an uproar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27504AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27504AJ\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>by advocating customs unlawful for us Romans<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27505AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27505AK\"></sup> to accept or practice.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27505AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27505AL\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The crowd joined in the attack against Paul and Silas, and the magistrates ordered them to be stripped and beaten with rods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27506AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27506AM\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>After they had been severely flogged, they were thrown into prison, and the jailer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27507AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27507AN\"></sup> was commanded to guard them carefully.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When he received these orders, he put them in the inner cell and fastened their feet in the stocks.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27508AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27508AO\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>About midnight<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27509AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27509AP\"></sup> Paul and Silas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27509AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27509AQ\"></sup> were praying and singing hymns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27509AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27509AR\"></sup> to God, and the other prisoners were listening to them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Suddenly there was such a violent earthquake that the foundations of the prison were shaken.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27510AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27510AS\"></sup> At once all the prison doors flew open,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27510AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27510AT\"></sup> and everyone’s chains came loose.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27510AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27510AU\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The jailer woke up, and when he saw the prison doors open, he drew his sword and was about to kill himself because he thought the prisoners had escaped.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27511AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27511AV\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But Paul shouted, “Don’t harm yourself! We are all here!”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The jailer called for lights, rushed in and fell trembling before Paul and Silas.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27513AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27513AW\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He then brought them out and asked, “Sirs, what must I do to be saved?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27514AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27514AX\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>They replied, “Believe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27515AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27515AY\"></sup> in the Lord Jesus, and you will be saved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27515AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27515AZ\"></sup>—you and your household.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27515BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27515BA\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then they spoke the word of the Lord to him and to all the others in his house.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>At that hour of the night<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27517BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27517BB\"></sup> the jailer took them and washed their wounds; then immediately he and all his household were baptized.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27517BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27517BC\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The jailer brought them into his house and set a meal before them; he<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27518BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27518BD\"></sup> was filled with joy because he had come to believe in God—he and his whole household.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>When it was daylight, the magistrates sent their officers to the jailer with the order: “Release those men.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The jailer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27520BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27520BE\"></sup> told Paul, “The magistrates have ordered that you and Silas be released. Now you can leave. Go in peace.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27520BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27520BF\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But Paul said to the officers: “They beat us publicly without a trial, even though we are Roman citizens,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27521BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27521BG\"></sup> and threw us into prison. And now do they want to get rid of us quietly? No! Let them come themselves and escort us out.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The officers reported this to the magistrates, and when they heard that Paul and Silas were Roman citizens, they were alarmed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27522BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27522BH\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>They came to appease them and escorted them from the prison, requesting them to leave the city.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27523BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27523BI\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>After Paul and Silas came out of the prison, they went to Lydia’s house,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27524BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27524BJ\"></sup> where they met with the brothers and sisters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27524BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27524BK\"></sup> and encouraged them. Then they left."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>When Paul and his companions had passed through Amphipolis and Apollonia, they came to Thessalonica,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27525A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27525A\"></sup> where there was a Jewish synagogue.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>As was his custom, Paul went into the synagogue,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27526B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27526B\"></sup> and on three Sabbath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27526C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27526C\"></sup> days he reasoned with them from the Scriptures,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27526D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27526D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>explaining and proving that the Messiah had to suffer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27527E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27527E\"></sup> and rise from the dead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27527F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27527F\"></sup> “This Jesus I am proclaiming to you is the Messiah,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27527G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27527G\"></sup> he said.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Some of the Jews were persuaded and joined Paul and Silas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27528H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27528H\"></sup> as did a large number of God-fearing Greeks and quite a few prominent women.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But other Jews were jealous; so they rounded up some bad characters from the marketplace, formed a mob and started a riot in the city.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27529I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27529I\"></sup> They rushed to Jason’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27529J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27529J\"></sup> house in search of Paul and Silas in order to bring them out to the crowd.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But when they did not find them, they dragged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27530K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27530K\"></sup> Jason and some other believers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27530L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27530L\"></sup> before the city officials, shouting: “These men who have caused trouble all over the world<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27530M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27530M\"></sup> have now come here,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27530N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27530N\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and Jason has welcomed them into his house. They are all defying Caesar’s decrees, saying that there is another king, one called Jesus.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27531O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27531O\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When they heard this, the crowd and the city officials were thrown into turmoil.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then they made Jason<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27533P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27533P\"></sup> and the others post bond and let them go.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As soon as it was night, the believers sent Paul and Silas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27534Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27534Q\"></sup> away to Berea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27534R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27534R\"></sup> On arriving there, they went to the Jewish synagogue.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27534S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27534S\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the Berean Jews were of more noble character than those in Thessalonica,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27535T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27535T\"></sup> for they received the message with great eagerness and examined the Scriptures<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27535U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27535U\"></sup> every day to see if what Paul said was true.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27535V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27535V\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>As a result, many of them believed, as did also a number of prominent Greek women and many Greek men.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27536W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27536W\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But when the Jews in Thessalonica learned that Paul was preaching the word of God at Berea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27537X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27537X\"></sup> some of them went there too, agitating the crowds and stirring them up.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The believers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27538Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27538Y\"></sup> immediately sent Paul to the coast, but Silas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27538Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27538Z\"></sup> and Timothy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27538AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27538AA\"></sup> stayed at Berea.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Those who escorted Paul brought him to Athens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27539AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27539AB\"></sup> and then left with instructions for Silas and Timothy to join him as soon as possible.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27539AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27539AC\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>While Paul was waiting for them in Athens, he was greatly distressed to see that the city was full of idols.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So he reasoned in the synagogue<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27541AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27541AD\"></sup> with both Jews and God-fearing Greeks, as well as in the marketplace day by day with those who happened to be there.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>A group of Epicurean and Stoic philosophers began to debate with him. Some of them asked, “What is this babbler trying to say?” Others remarked, “He seems to be advocating foreign gods.” They said this because Paul was preaching the good news<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27542AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27542AE\"></sup> about Jesus and the resurrection.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27542AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27542AF\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then they took him and brought him to a meeting of the Areopagus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27543AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27543AG\"></sup> where they said to him, “May we know what this new teaching<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27543AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27543AH\"></sup> is that you are presenting?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You are bringing some strange ideas to our ears, and we would like to know what they mean.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>(All the Athenians<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27545AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27545AI\"></sup> and the foreigners who lived there spent their time doing nothing but talking about and listening to the latest ideas.)",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Paul then stood up in the meeting of the Areopagus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27546AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27546AJ\"></sup> and said: “People of Athens! I see that in every way you are very religious.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27546AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27546AK\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For as I walked around and looked carefully at your objects of worship, I even found an altar with this inscription: <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">to an unknown god</span>. So you are ignorant of the very thing you worship<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27547AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27547AL\"></sup>—and this is what I am going to proclaim to you.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“The God who made the world and everything in it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27548AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27548AM\"></sup> is the Lord of heaven and earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27548AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27548AN\"></sup> and does not live in temples built by human hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27548AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27548AO\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And he is not served by human hands, as if he needed anything. Rather, he himself gives everyone life and breath and everything else.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27549AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27549AP\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>From one man he made all the nations, that they should inhabit the whole earth; and he marked out their appointed times in history and the boundaries of their lands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27550AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27550AQ\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>God did this so that they would seek him and perhaps reach out for him and find him, though he is not far from any one of us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27551AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27551AR\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>‘For in him we live and move and have our being.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27552AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27552AS\"></sup> As some of your own poets have said, ‘We are his offspring.’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Therefore since we are God’s offspring, we should not think that the divine being is like gold or silver or stone—an image made by human design and skill.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27553AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27553AT\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>In the past God overlooked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27554AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27554AU\"></sup> such ignorance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27554AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27554AV\"></sup> but now he commands all people everywhere to repent.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27554AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27554AW\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For he has set a day when he will judge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27555AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27555AX\"></sup> the world with justice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27555AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27555AY\"></sup> by the man he has appointed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27555AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27555AZ\"></sup> He has given proof of this to everyone by raising him from the dead.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27555BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27555BA\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When they heard about the resurrection of the dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27556BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27556BB\"></sup> some of them sneered, but others said, “We want to hear you again on this subject.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>At that, Paul left the Council.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Some of the people became followers of Paul and believed. Among them was Dionysius, a member of the Areopagus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27558BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27558BC\"></sup> also a woman named Damaris, and a number of others."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>After this, Paul left Athens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27559A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27559A\"></sup> and went to Corinth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27559B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27559B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>There he met a Jew named Aquila, a native of Pontus, who had recently come from Italy with his wife Priscilla,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27560C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27560C\"></sup> because Claudius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27560D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27560D\"></sup> had ordered all Jews to leave Rome. Paul went to see them,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and because he was a tentmaker as they were, he stayed and worked with them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27561E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27561E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Every Sabbath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27562F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27562F\"></sup> he reasoned in the synagogue,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27562G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27562G\"></sup> trying to persuade Jews and Greeks.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Silas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27563H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27563H\"></sup> and Timothy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27563I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27563I\"></sup> came from Macedonia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27563J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27563J\"></sup> Paul devoted himself exclusively to preaching, testifying to the Jews that Jesus was the Messiah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27563K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27563K\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But when they opposed Paul and became abusive,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27564L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27564L\"></sup> he shook out his clothes in protest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27564M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27564M\"></sup> and said to them, “Your blood be on your own heads!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27564N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27564N\"></sup> I am innocent of it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27564O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27564O\"></sup> From now on I will go to the Gentiles.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27564P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27564P\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Paul left the synagogue and went next door to the house of Titius Justus, a worshiper of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27565Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27565Q\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Crispus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27566R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27566R\"></sup> the synagogue leader,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27566S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27566S\"></sup> and his entire household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27566T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27566T\"></sup> believed in the Lord; and many of the Corinthians who heard Paul believed and were baptized.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>One night the Lord spoke to Paul in a vision:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27567U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27567U\"></sup> <span class=\"woj\">“Do not be afraid;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27567V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27567V\"></sup> keep on speaking, do not be silent.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For I am with you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27568W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27568W\"></sup> and no one is going to attack and harm you, because I have many people in this city.”</span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Paul stayed in Corinth for a year and a half, teaching them the word of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27569X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27569X\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>While Gallio was proconsul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27570Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27570Y\"></sup> of Achaia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27570Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27570Z\"></sup> the Jews of Corinth made a united attack on Paul and brought him to the place of judgment.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“This man,” they charged, “is persuading the people to worship God in ways contrary to the law.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Just as Paul was about to speak, Gallio said to them, “If you Jews were making a complaint about some misdemeanor or serious crime, it would be reasonable for me to listen to you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But since it involves questions about words and names and your own law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27573AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27573AA\"></sup>—settle the matter yourselves. I will not be a judge of such things.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So he drove them off.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the crowd there turned on Sosthenes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27575AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27575AB\"></sup> the synagogue leader<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27575AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27575AC\"></sup> and beat him in front of the proconsul; and Gallio showed no concern whatever.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Paul stayed on in Corinth for some time. Then he left the brothers and sisters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27576AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27576AD\"></sup> and sailed for Syria,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27576AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27576AE\"></sup> accompanied by Priscilla and Aquila.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27576AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27576AF\"></sup> Before he sailed, he had his hair cut off at Cenchreae<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27576AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27576AG\"></sup> because of a vow he had taken.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27576AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27576AH\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They arrived at Ephesus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27577AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27577AI\"></sup> where Paul left Priscilla and Aquila. He himself went into the synagogue and reasoned with the Jews.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When they asked him to spend more time with them, he declined.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But as he left, he promised, “I will come back if it is God’s will.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27579AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27579AJ\"></sup> Then he set sail from Ephesus.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When he landed at Caesarea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27580AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27580AK\"></sup> he went up to Jerusalem and greeted the church and then went down to Antioch.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27580AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27580AL\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>After spending some time in Antioch, Paul set out from there and traveled from place to place throughout the region of Galatia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27581AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27581AM\"></sup> and Phrygia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27581AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27581AN\"></sup> strengthening all the disciples.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27581AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27581AO\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Meanwhile a Jew named Apollos,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27582AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27582AP\"></sup> a native of Alexandria, came to Ephesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27582AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27582AQ\"></sup> He was a learned man, with a thorough knowledge of the Scriptures.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He had been instructed in the way of the Lord, and he spoke with great fervor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27583AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27583AR\"></sup> and taught about Jesus accurately, though he knew only the baptism of John.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27583AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27583AS\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He began to speak boldly in the synagogue. When Priscilla and Aquila<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27584AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27584AT\"></sup> heard him, they invited him to their home and explained to him the way of God more adequately.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When Apollos wanted to go to Achaia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27585AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27585AU\"></sup> the brothers and sisters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27585AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27585AV\"></sup> encouraged him and wrote to the disciples there to welcome him. When he arrived, he was a great help to those who by grace had believed.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For he vigorously refuted his Jewish opponents in public debate, proving from the Scriptures<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27586AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27586AW\"></sup> that Jesus was the Messiah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27586AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27586AX\"></sup>"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>While Apollos<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27587A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27587A\"></sup> was at Corinth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27587B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27587B\"></sup> Paul took the road through the interior and arrived at Ephesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27587C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27587C\"></sup> There he found some disciples",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and asked them, “Did you receive the Holy Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27588D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27588D\"></sup> when you believed?”They answered, “No, we have not even heard that there is a Holy Spirit.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Paul asked, “Then what baptism did you receive?”“John’s baptism,” they replied.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Paul said, “John’s baptism<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27590E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27590E\"></sup> was a baptism of repentance. He told the people to believe in the one coming after him, that is, in Jesus.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27590F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27590F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>On hearing this, they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27591G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27591G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Paul placed his hands on them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27592H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27592H\"></sup> the Holy Spirit came on them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27592I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27592I\"></sup> and they spoke in tongues<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27592J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27592J\"></sup> and prophesied.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>There were about twelve men in all.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Paul entered the synagogue<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27594K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27594K\"></sup> and spoke boldly there for three months, arguing persuasively about the kingdom of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27594L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27594L\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But some of them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27595M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27595M\"></sup> became obstinate; they refused to believe and publicly maligned the Way.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27595N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27595N\"></sup> So Paul left them. He took the disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27595O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27595O\"></sup> with him and had discussions daily in the lecture hall of Tyrannus.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>This went on for two years,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27596P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27596P\"></sup> so that all the Jews and Greeks who lived in the province of Asia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27596Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27596Q\"></sup> heard the word of the Lord.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27596R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27596R\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>God did extraordinary miracles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27597S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27597S\"></sup> through Paul,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>so that even handkerchiefs and aprons that had touched him were taken to the sick, and their illnesses were cured<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27598T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27598T\"></sup> and the evil spirits left them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Some Jews who went around driving out evil spirits<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27599U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27599U\"></sup> tried to invoke the name of the Lord Jesus over those who were demon-possessed. They would say, “In the name of the Jesus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27599V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27599V\"></sup> whom Paul preaches, I command you to come out.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Seven sons of Sceva, a Jewish chief priest, were doing this.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>One day the evil spirit answered them, “Jesus I know, and Paul I know about, but who are you?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the man who had the evil spirit jumped on them and overpowered them all. He gave them such a beating that they ran out of the house naked and bleeding.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When this became known to the Jews and Greeks living in Ephesus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27603W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27603W\"></sup> they were all seized with fear,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27603X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27603X\"></sup> and the name of the Lord Jesus was held in high honor.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Many of those who believed now came and openly confessed what they had done.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>A number who had practiced sorcery brought their scrolls together and burned them publicly. When they calculated the value of the scrolls, the total came to fifty thousand drachmas.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In this way the word of the Lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27606Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27606Y\"></sup> spread widely and grew in power.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27606Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27606Z\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>After all this had happened, Paul decided to go to Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27607AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27607AA\"></sup> passing through Macedonia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27607AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27607AB\"></sup> and Achaia.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27607AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27607AC\"></sup> “After I have been there,” he said, “I must visit Rome also.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27607AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27607AD\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He sent two of his helpers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27608AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27608AE\"></sup> Timothy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27608AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27608AF\"></sup> and Erastus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27608AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27608AG\"></sup> to Macedonia, while he stayed in the province of Asia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27608AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27608AH\"></sup> a little longer.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>About that time there arose a great disturbance about the Way.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27609AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27609AI\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>A silversmith named Demetrius, who made silver shrines of Artemis, brought in a lot of business for the craftsmen there.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He called them together, along with the workers in related trades, and said: “You know, my friends, that we receive a good income from this business.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27611AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27611AJ\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And you see and hear how this fellow Paul has convinced and led astray large numbers of people here in Ephesus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27612AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27612AK\"></sup> and in practically the whole province of Asia.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27612AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27612AL\"></sup> He says that gods made by human hands are no gods at all.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27612AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27612AM\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>There is danger not only that our trade will lose its good name, but also that the temple of the great goddess Artemis will be discredited; and the goddess herself, who is worshiped throughout the province of Asia and the world, will be robbed of her divine majesty.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When they heard this, they were furious and began shouting: “Great is Artemis of the Ephesians!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27614AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27614AN\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Soon the whole city was in an uproar. The people seized Gaius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27615AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27615AO\"></sup> and Aristarchus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27615AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27615AP\"></sup> Paul’s traveling companions from Macedonia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27615AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27615AQ\"></sup> and all of them rushed into the theater together.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Paul wanted to appear before the crowd, but the disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27616AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27616AR\"></sup> would not let him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Even some of the officials of the province, friends of Paul, sent him a message begging him not to venture into the theater.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The assembly was in confusion: Some were shouting one thing, some another.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27618AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27618AS\"></sup> Most of the people did not even know why they were there.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The Jews in the crowd pushed Alexander to the front, and they shouted instructions to him. He motioned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27619AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27619AT\"></sup> for silence in order to make a defense before the people.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But when they realized he was a Jew, they all shouted in unison for about two hours: “Great is Artemis of the Ephesians!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27620AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27620AU\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The city clerk quieted the crowd and said: “Fellow Ephesians,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27621AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27621AV\"></sup> doesn’t all the world know that the city of Ephesus is the guardian of the temple of the great Artemis and of her image, which fell from heaven?",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Therefore, since these facts are undeniable, you ought to calm down and not do anything rash.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>You have brought these men here, though they have neither robbed temples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27623AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27623AW\"></sup> nor blasphemed our goddess.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>If, then, Demetrius and his fellow craftsmen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27624AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27624AX\"></sup> have a grievance against anybody, the courts are open and there are proconsuls.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27624AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27624AY\"></sup> They can press charges.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>If there is anything further you want to bring up, it must be settled in a legal assembly.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>As it is, we are in danger of being charged with rioting because of what happened today. In that case we would not be able to account for this commotion, since there is no reason for it.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>After he had said this, he dismissed the assembly."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>When the uproar had ended, Paul sent for the disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27628A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27628A\"></sup> and, after encouraging them, said goodbye and set out for Macedonia.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27628B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27628B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He traveled through that area, speaking many words of encouragement to the people, and finally arrived in Greece,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>where he stayed three months. Because some Jews had plotted against him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27630C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27630C\"></sup> just as he was about to sail for Syria,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27630D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27630D\"></sup> he decided to go back through Macedonia.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27630E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27630E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He was accompanied by Sopater son of Pyrrhus from Berea, Aristarchus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27631F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27631F\"></sup> and Secundus from Thessalonica,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27631G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27631G\"></sup> Gaius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27631H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27631H\"></sup> from Derbe, Timothy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27631I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27631I\"></sup> also, and Tychicus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27631J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27631J\"></sup> and Trophimus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27631K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27631K\"></sup> from the province of Asia.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27631L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27631L\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>These men went on ahead and waited for us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27632M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27632M\"></sup> at Troas.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27632N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27632N\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But we sailed from Philippi<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27633O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27633O\"></sup> after the Festival of Unleavened Bread, and five days later joined the others at Troas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27633P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27633P\"></sup> where we stayed seven days.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>On the first day of the week<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27634Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27634Q\"></sup> we came together to break bread.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27634R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27634R\"></sup> Paul spoke to the people and, because he intended to leave the next day, kept on talking until midnight.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>There were many lamps in the upstairs room<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27635S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27635S\"></sup> where we were meeting.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Seated in a window was a young man named Eutychus, who was sinking into a deep sleep as Paul talked on and on. When he was sound asleep, he fell to the ground from the third story and was picked up dead.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Paul went down, threw himself on the young man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27637T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27637T\"></sup> and put his arms around him. “Don’t be alarmed,” he said. “He’s alive!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27637U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27637U\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then he went upstairs again and broke bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27638V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27638V\"></sup> and ate. After talking until daylight, he left.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The people took the young man home alive and were greatly comforted.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>We went on ahead to the ship and sailed for Assos, where we were going to take Paul aboard. He had made this arrangement because he was going there on foot.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When he met us at Assos, we took him aboard and went on to Mitylene.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The next day we set sail from there and arrived off Chios. The day after that we crossed over to Samos, and on the following day arrived at Miletus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27642W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27642W\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Paul had decided to sail past Ephesus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27643X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27643X\"></sup> to avoid spending time in the province of Asia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27643Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27643Y\"></sup> for he was in a hurry to reach Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27643Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27643Z\"></sup> if possible, by the day of Pentecost.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27643AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27643AA\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>From Miletus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27644AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27644AB\"></sup> Paul sent to Ephesus for the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27644AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27644AC\"></sup> of the church.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When they arrived, he said to them: “You know how I lived the whole time I was with you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27645AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27645AD\"></sup> from the first day I came into the province of Asia.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27645AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27645AE\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I served the Lord with great humility and with tears<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27646AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27646AF\"></sup> and in the midst of severe testing by the plots of my Jewish opponents.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27646AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27646AG\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You know that I have not hesitated to preach anything<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27647AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27647AH\"></sup> that would be helpful to you but have taught you publicly and from house to house.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I have declared to both Jews<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27648AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27648AI\"></sup> and Greeks that they must turn to God in repentance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27648AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27648AJ\"></sup> and have faith in our Lord Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27648AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27648AK\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“And now, compelled by the Spirit, I am going to Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27649AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27649AL\"></sup> not knowing what will happen to me there.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>I only know that in every city the Holy Spirit warns me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27650AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27650AM\"></sup> that prison and hardships are facing me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27650AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27650AN\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>However, I consider my life worth nothing to me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27651AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27651AO\"></sup> my only aim is to finish the race<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27651AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27651AP\"></sup> and complete the task<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27651AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27651AQ\"></sup> the Lord Jesus has given me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27651AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27651AR\"></sup>—the task of testifying to the good news of God’s grace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27651AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27651AS\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Now I know that none of you among whom I have gone about preaching the kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27652AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27652AT\"></sup> will ever see me again.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27652AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27652AU\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Therefore, I declare to you today that I am innocent of the blood of any of you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27653AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27653AV\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For I have not hesitated to proclaim to you the whole will of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27654AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27654AW\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Keep watch over yourselves and all the flock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27655AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27655AX\"></sup> of which the Holy Spirit has made you overseers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27655AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27655AY\"></sup> Be shepherds of the church of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27655AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27655AZ\"></sup> which he bought<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27655BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27655BA\"></sup> with his own blood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27655BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27655BB\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>I know that after I leave, savage wolves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27656BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27656BC\"></sup> will come in among you and will not spare the flock.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27656BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27656BD\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Even from your own number men will arise and distort the truth in order to draw away disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27657BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27657BE\"></sup> after them.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So be on your guard! Remember that for three years<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27658BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27658BF\"></sup> I never stopped warning each of you night and day with tears.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27658BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27658BG\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Now I commit you to God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27659BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27659BH\"></sup> and to the word of his grace, which can build you up and give you an inheritance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27659BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27659BI\"></sup> among all those who are sanctified.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27659BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27659BJ\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>I have not coveted anyone’s silver or gold or clothing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27660BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27660BK\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>You yourselves know that these hands of mine have supplied my own needs and the needs of my companions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27661BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27661BL\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>In everything I did, I showed you that by this kind of hard work we must help the weak, remembering the words the Lord Jesus himself said: <span class=\"woj\">‘It is more blessed to give than to receive.’</span> ”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>When Paul had finished speaking, he knelt down with all of them and prayed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27663BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27663BM\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They all wept as they embraced him and kissed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27664BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27664BN\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>What grieved them most was his statement that they would never see his face again.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27665BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27665BO\"></sup> Then they accompanied him to the ship.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27665BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27665BP\"></sup>"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>After we<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27666A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27666A\"></sup> had torn ourselves away from them, we put out to sea and sailed straight to Kos. The next day we went to Rhodes and from there to Patara.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>We found a ship crossing over to Phoenicia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27667B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27667B\"></sup> went on board and set sail.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>After sighting Cyprus and passing to the south of it, we sailed on to Syria.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27668C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27668C\"></sup> We landed at Tyre, where our ship was to unload its cargo.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>We sought out the disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27669D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27669D\"></sup> there and stayed with them seven days. Through the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27669E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27669E\"></sup> they urged Paul not to go on to Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When it was time to leave, we left and continued on our way. All of them, including wives and children, accompanied us out of the city, and there on the beach we knelt to pray.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27670F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27670F\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>After saying goodbye to each other, we went aboard the ship, and they returned home.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>We continued our voyage from Tyre<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27672G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27672G\"></sup> and landed at Ptolemais, where we greeted the brothers and sisters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27672H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27672H\"></sup> and stayed with them for a day.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Leaving the next day, we reached Caesarea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27673I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27673I\"></sup> and stayed at the house of Philip<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27673J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27673J\"></sup> the evangelist,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27673K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27673K\"></sup> one of the Seven.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He had four unmarried daughters who prophesied.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27674L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27674L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>After we had been there a number of days, a prophet named Agabus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27675M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27675M\"></sup> came down from Judea.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Coming over to us, he took Paul’s belt, tied his own hands and feet with it and said, “The Holy Spirit says,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27676N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27676N\"></sup> ‘In this way the Jewish leaders in Jerusalem will bind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27676O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27676O\"></sup> the owner of this belt and will hand him over to the Gentiles.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27676P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27676P\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When we heard this, we and the people there pleaded with Paul not to go up to Jerusalem.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Paul answered, “Why are you weeping and breaking my heart? I am ready not only to be bound, but also to die<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27678Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27678Q\"></sup> in Jerusalem for the name of the Lord Jesus.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27678R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27678R\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When he would not be dissuaded, we gave up<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27679S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27679S\"></sup> and said, “The Lord’s will be done.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27679T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27679T\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>After this, we started on our way up to Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27680U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27680U\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Some of the disciples from Caesarea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27681V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27681V\"></sup> accompanied us and brought us to the home of Mnason, where we were to stay. He was a man from Cyprus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27681W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27681W\"></sup> and one of the early disciples.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When we arrived at Jerusalem, the brothers and sisters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27682X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27682X\"></sup> received us warmly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27682Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27682Y\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The next day Paul and the rest of us went to see James,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27683Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27683Z\"></sup> and all the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27683AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27683AA\"></sup> were present.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Paul greeted them and reported in detail what God had done among the Gentiles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27684AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27684AB\"></sup> through his ministry.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27684AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27684AC\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When they heard this, they praised God. Then they said to Paul: “You see, brother, how many thousands of Jews have believed, and all of them are zealous<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27685AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27685AD\"></sup> for the law.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27685AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27685AE\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They have been informed that you teach all the Jews who live among the Gentiles to turn away from Moses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27686AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27686AF\"></sup> telling them not to circumcise their children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27686AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27686AG\"></sup> or live according to our customs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27686AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27686AH\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>What shall we do? They will certainly hear that you have come,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>so do what we tell you. There are four men with us who have made a vow.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27688AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27688AI\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Take these men, join in their purification rites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27689AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27689AJ\"></sup> and pay their expenses, so that they can have their heads shaved.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27689AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27689AK\"></sup> Then everyone will know there is no truth in these reports about you, but that you yourself are living in obedience to the law.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As for the Gentile believers, we have written to them our decision that they should abstain from food sacrificed to idols, from blood, from the meat of strangled animals and from sexual immorality.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27690AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27690AL\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The next day Paul took the men and purified himself along with them. Then he went to the temple to give notice of the date when the days of purification would end and the offering would be made for each of them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27691AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27691AM\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When the seven days were nearly over, some Jews from the province of Asia saw Paul at the temple. They stirred up the whole crowd and seized him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27692AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27692AN\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>shouting, “Fellow Israelites, help us! This is the man who teaches everyone everywhere against our people and our law and this place. And besides, he has brought Greeks into the temple and defiled this holy place.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27693AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27693AO\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>(They had previously seen Trophimus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27694AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27694AP\"></sup> the Ephesian<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27694AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27694AQ\"></sup> in the city with Paul and assumed that Paul had brought him into the temple.)",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The whole city was aroused, and the people came running from all directions. Seizing Paul,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27695AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27695AR\"></sup> they dragged him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27695AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27695AS\"></sup> from the temple, and immediately the gates were shut.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>While they were trying to kill him, news reached the commander of the Roman troops that the whole city of Jerusalem was in an uproar.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He at once took some officers and soldiers and ran down to the crowd. When the rioters saw the commander and his soldiers, they stopped beating Paul.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27697AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27697AT\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The commander came up and arrested him and ordered him to be bound<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27698AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27698AU\"></sup> with two<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27698AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27698AV\"></sup> chains.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27698AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27698AW\"></sup> Then he asked who he was and what he had done.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Some in the crowd shouted one thing and some another,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27699AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27699AX\"></sup> and since the commander could not get at the truth because of the uproar, he ordered that Paul be taken into the barracks.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27699AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27699AY\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>When Paul reached the steps,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27700AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27700AZ\"></sup> the violence of the mob was so great he had to be carried by the soldiers.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The crowd that followed kept shouting, “Get rid of him!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27701BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27701BA\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>As the soldiers were about to take Paul into the barracks,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27702BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27702BC\"></sup> he asked the commander, “May I say something to you?”“Do you speak Greek?” he replied.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“Aren’t you the Egyptian who started a revolt and led four thousand terrorists out into the wilderness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27703BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27703BD\"></sup> some time ago?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27703BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27703BE\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Paul answered, “I am a Jew, from Tarsus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27704BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27704BF\"></sup> in Cilicia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27704BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27704BG\"></sup> a citizen of no ordinary city. Please let me speak to the people.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>After receiving the commander’s permission, Paul stood on the steps and motioned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27705BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27705BH\"></sup> to the crowd. When they were all silent, he said to them in Aramaic:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27705BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27705BI\"></sup>"
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum mid-paragraph\">22 </span><sup class=\"versenum mid-paragraph\">1 </sup>“Brothers and fathers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27706A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27706A\"></sup> listen now to my defense.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When they heard him speak to them in Aramaic,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27707B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27707B\"></sup> they became very quiet.Then Paul said:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“I am a Jew,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27708C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27708C\"></sup> born in Tarsus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27708D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27708D\"></sup> of Cilicia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27708E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27708E\"></sup> but brought up in this city. I studied under<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27708F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27708F\"></sup> Gamaliel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27708G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27708G\"></sup> and was thoroughly trained in the law of our ancestors.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27708H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27708H\"></sup> I was just as zealous<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27708I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27708I\"></sup> for God as any of you are today.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I persecuted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27709J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27709J\"></sup> the followers of this Way<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27709K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27709K\"></sup> to their death, arresting both men and women and throwing them into prison,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27709L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27709L\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>as the high priest and all the Council<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27710M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27710M\"></sup> can themselves testify. I even obtained letters from them to their associates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27710N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27710N\"></sup> in Damascus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27710O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27710O\"></sup> and went there to bring these people as prisoners to Jerusalem to be punished.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“About noon as I came near Damascus, suddenly a bright light from heaven flashed around me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27711P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27711P\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I fell to the ground and heard a voice say to me, <span class=\"woj\">‘Saul! Saul! Why do you persecute me?’</span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“‘Who are you, Lord?’ I asked.“ <span class=\"woj\">‘I am Jesus of Nazareth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27713Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27713Q\"></sup> whom you are persecuting,’</span> he replied.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>My companions saw the light,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27714R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27714R\"></sup> but they did not understand the voice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27714S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27714S\"></sup> of him who was speaking to me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“‘What shall I do, Lord?’ I asked.“ <span class=\"woj\">‘Get up,’</span> the Lord said, <span class=\"woj\">‘and go into Damascus. There you will be told all that you have been assigned to do.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27715T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27715T\"></sup></span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>My companions led me by the hand into Damascus, because the brilliance of the light had blinded me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27716U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27716U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“A man named Ananias came to see me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27717V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27717V\"></sup> He was a devout observer of the law and highly respected by all the Jews living there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27717W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27717W\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He stood beside me and said, ‘Brother Saul, receive your sight!’ And at that very moment I was able to see him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Then he said: ‘The God of our ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27719X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27719X\"></sup> has chosen you to know his will and to see<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27719Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27719Y\"></sup> the Righteous One<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27719Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27719Z\"></sup> and to hear words from his mouth.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You will be his witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27720AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27720AA\"></sup> to all people of what you have seen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27720AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27720AB\"></sup> and heard.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And now what are you waiting for? Get up, be baptized<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27721AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27721AC\"></sup> and wash your sins away,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27721AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27721AD\"></sup> calling on his name.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27721AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27721AE\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“When I returned to Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27722AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27722AF\"></sup> and was praying at the temple, I fell into a trance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27722AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27722AG\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and saw the Lord speaking to me. <span class=\"woj\">‘Quick!’</span> he said. <span class=\"woj\">‘Leave Jerusalem immediately, because the people here will not accept your testimony about me.’</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“‘Lord,’ I replied, ‘these people know that I went from one synagogue to another to imprison<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27724AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27724AH\"></sup> and beat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27724AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27724AI\"></sup> those who believe in you.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And when the blood of your martyr Stephen was shed, I stood there giving my approval and guarding the clothes of those who were killing him.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27725AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27725AJ\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Then the Lord said to me, <span class=\"woj\">‘Go; I will send you far away to the Gentiles.’ </span>”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27726AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27726AK\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The crowd listened to Paul until he said this. Then they raised their voices and shouted, “Rid the earth of him!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27727AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27727AL\"></sup> He’s not fit to live!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27727AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27727AM\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As they were shouting and throwing off their cloaks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27728AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27728AN\"></sup> and flinging dust into the air,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27728AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27728AO\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>the commander ordered that Paul be taken into the barracks.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27729AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27729AP\"></sup> He directed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27729AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27729AQ\"></sup> that he be flogged and interrogated in order to find out why the people were shouting at him like this.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As they stretched him out to flog him, Paul said to the centurion standing there, “Is it legal for you to flog a Roman citizen who hasn’t even been found guilty?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27730AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27730AR\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When the centurion heard this, he went to the commander and reported it. “What are you going to do?” he asked. “This man is a Roman citizen.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The commander went to Paul and asked, “Tell me, are you a Roman citizen?”“Yes, I am,” he answered.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the commander said, “I had to pay a lot of money for my citizenship.”“But I was born a citizen,” Paul replied.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Those who were about to interrogate him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27734AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27734AS\"></sup> withdrew immediately. The commander himself was alarmed when he realized that he had put Paul, a Roman citizen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27734AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27734AT\"></sup> in chains.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27734AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27734AU\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The commander wanted to find out exactly why Paul was being accused by the Jews.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27735AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27735AV\"></sup> So the next day he released him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27735AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27735AW\"></sup> and ordered the chief priests and all the members of the Sanhedrin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27735AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27735AX\"></sup> to assemble. Then he brought Paul and had him stand before them."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>Paul looked straight at the Sanhedrin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27736A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27736A\"></sup> and said, “My brothers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27736B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27736B\"></sup> I have fulfilled my duty to God in all good conscience<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27736C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27736C\"></sup> to this day.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>At this the high priest Ananias<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27737D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27737D\"></sup> ordered those standing near Paul to strike him on the mouth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27737E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27737E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Paul said to him, “God will strike you, you whitewashed wall!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27738F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27738F\"></sup> You sit there to judge me according to the law, yet you yourself violate the law by commanding that I be struck!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27738G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27738G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Those who were standing near Paul said, “How dare you insult God’s high priest!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Paul replied, “Brothers, I did not realize that he was the high priest; for it is written: ‘Do not speak evil about the ruler of your people.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27740H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27740H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Paul, knowing that some of them were Sadducees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27741I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27741I\"></sup> and the others Pharisees, called out in the Sanhedrin, “My brothers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27741J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27741J\"></sup> I am a Pharisee,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27741K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27741K\"></sup> descended from Pharisees. I stand on trial because of the hope of the resurrection of the dead.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27741L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27741L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When he said this, a dispute broke out between the Pharisees and the Sadducees, and the assembly was divided.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>(The Sadducees say that there is no resurrection,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27743M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27743M\"></sup> and that there are neither angels nor spirits, but the Pharisees believe all these things.)",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>There was a great uproar, and some of the teachers of the law who were Pharisees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27744N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27744N\"></sup> stood up and argued vigorously. “We find nothing wrong with this man,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27744O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27744O\"></sup> they said. “What if a spirit or an angel has spoken to him?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27744P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27744P\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The dispute became so violent that the commander was afraid Paul would be torn to pieces by them. He ordered the troops to go down and take him away from them by force and bring him into the barracks.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27745Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27745Q\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The following night the Lord stood near Paul and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Take courage!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27746R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27746R\"></sup> As you have testified about me in Jerusalem, so you must also testify in Rome.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27746S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27746S\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The next morning some Jews formed a conspiracy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27747T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27747T\"></sup> and bound themselves with an oath not to eat or drink until they had killed Paul.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27747U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27747U\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>More than forty men were involved in this plot.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They went to the chief priests and the elders and said, “We have taken a solemn oath not to eat anything until we have killed Paul.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27749V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27749V\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now then, you and the Sanhedrin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27750W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27750W\"></sup> petition the commander to bring him before you on the pretext of wanting more accurate information about his case. We are ready to kill him before he gets here.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But when the son of Paul’s sister heard of this plot, he went into the barracks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27751X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27751X\"></sup> and told Paul.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Paul called one of the centurions and said, “Take this young man to the commander; he has something to tell him.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So he took him to the commander.The centurion said, “Paul, the prisoner,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27753Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27753Y\"></sup> sent for me and asked me to bring this young man to you because he has something to tell you.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The commander took the young man by the hand, drew him aside and asked, “What is it you want to tell me?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He said: “Some Jews have agreed to ask you to bring Paul before the Sanhedrin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27755Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27755Z\"></sup> tomorrow on the pretext of wanting more accurate information about him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27755AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27755AA\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Don’t give in to them, because more than forty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27756AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27756AB\"></sup> of them are waiting in ambush for him. They have taken an oath not to eat or drink until they have killed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27756AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27756AC\"></sup> They are ready now, waiting for your consent to their request.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The commander dismissed the young man with this warning: “Don’t tell anyone that you have reported this to me.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then he called two of his centurions and ordered them, “Get ready a detachment of two hundred soldiers, seventy horsemen and two hundred spearmen to go to Caesarea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27758AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27758AD\"></sup> at nine tonight.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27758AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27758AE\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Provide horses for Paul so that he may be taken safely to Governor Felix.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27759AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27759AF\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He wrote a letter as follows:",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Claudius Lysias,To His Excellency,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27761AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27761AG\"></sup> Governor Felix:Greetings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27761AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27761AH\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>This man was seized by the Jews and they were about to kill him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27762AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27762AI\"></sup> but I came with my troops and rescued him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27762AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27762AJ\"></sup> for I had learned that he is a Roman citizen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27762AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27762AK\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I wanted to know why they were accusing him, so I brought him to their Sanhedrin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27763AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27763AL\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>I found that the accusation had to do with questions about their law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27764AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27764AM\"></sup> but there was no charge against him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27764AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27764AN\"></sup> that deserved death or imprisonment.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When I was informed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27765AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27765AO\"></sup> of a plot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27765AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27765AP\"></sup> to be carried out against the man, I sent him to you at once. I also ordered his accusers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27765AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27765AQ\"></sup> to present to you their case against him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So the soldiers, carrying out their orders, took Paul with them during the night and brought him as far as Antipatris.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The next day they let the cavalry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27767AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27767AR\"></sup> go on with him, while they returned to the barracks.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27767AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27767AS\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When the cavalry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27768AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27768AT\"></sup> arrived in Caesarea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27768AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27768AU\"></sup> they delivered the letter to the governor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27768AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27768AV\"></sup> and handed Paul over to him.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The governor read the letter and asked what province he was from. Learning that he was from Cilicia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27769AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27769AW\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>he said, “I will hear your case when your accusers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27770AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27770AX\"></sup> get here.” Then he ordered that Paul be kept under guard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27770AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27770AY\"></sup> in Herod’s palace."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Five days later the high priest Ananias<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27771A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27771A\"></sup> went down to Caesarea with some of the elders and a lawyer named Tertullus, and they brought their charges<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27771B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27771B\"></sup> against Paul before the governor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27771C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27771C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When Paul was called in, Tertullus presented his case before Felix: “We have enjoyed a long period of peace under you, and your foresight has brought about reforms in this nation.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Everywhere and in every way, most excellent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27773D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27773D\"></sup> Felix, we acknowledge this with profound gratitude.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But in order not to weary you further, I would request that you be kind enough to hear us briefly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“We have found this man to be a troublemaker, stirring up riots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27775E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27775E\"></sup> among the Jews<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27775F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27775F\"></sup> all over the world. He is a ringleader of the Nazarene<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27775G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27775G\"></sup> sect<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27775H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27775H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and even tried to desecrate the temple;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27776I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27776I\"></sup> so we seized him.<sup class=\"versenum\">[7] </sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>By examining him yourself you will be able to learn the truth about all these charges we are bringing against him.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The other Jews joined in the accusation,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27779J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27779J\"></sup> asserting that these things were true.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When the governor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27780K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27780K\"></sup> motioned for him to speak, Paul replied: “I know that for a number of years you have been a judge over this nation; so I gladly make my defense.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You can easily verify that no more than twelve days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27781L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27781L\"></sup> ago I went up to Jerusalem to worship.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>My accusers did not find me arguing with anyone at the temple,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27782M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27782M\"></sup> or stirring up a crowd<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27782N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27782N\"></sup> in the synagogues or anywhere else in the city.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And they cannot prove to you the charges they are now making against me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27783O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27783O\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>However, I admit that I worship the God of our ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27784P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27784P\"></sup> as a follower of the Way,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27784Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27784Q\"></sup> which they call a sect.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27784R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27784R\"></sup> I believe everything that is in accordance with the Law and that is written in the Prophets,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27784S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27784S\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and I have the same hope in God as these men themselves have, that there will be a resurrection<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27785T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27785T\"></sup> of both the righteous and the wicked.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27785U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27785U\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So I strive always to keep my conscience clear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27786V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27786V\"></sup> before God and man.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“After an absence of several years, I came to Jerusalem to bring my people gifts for the poor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27787W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27787W\"></sup> and to present offerings.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I was ceremonially clean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27788X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27788X\"></sup> when they found me in the temple courts doing this. There was no crowd with me, nor was I involved in any disturbance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27788Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27788Y\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But there are some Jews from the province of Asia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27789Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27789Z\"></sup> who ought to be here before you and bring charges if they have anything against me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27789AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27789AA\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Or these who are here should state what crime they found in me when I stood before the Sanhedrin—",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>unless it was this one thing I shouted as I stood in their presence: ‘It is concerning the resurrection of the dead that I am on trial before you today.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27791AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27791AB\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Felix, who was well acquainted with the Way,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27792AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27792AC\"></sup> adjourned the proceedings. “When Lysias the commander comes,” he said, “I will decide your case.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He ordered the centurion to keep Paul under guard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27793AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27793AD\"></sup> but to give him some freedom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27793AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27793AE\"></sup> and permit his friends to take care of his needs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27793AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27793AF\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Several days later Felix came with his wife Drusilla, who was Jewish. He sent for Paul and listened to him as he spoke about faith in Christ Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27794AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27794AG\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As Paul talked about righteousness, self-control<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27795AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27795AH\"></sup> and the judgment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27795AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27795AI\"></sup> to come, Felix was afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27795AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27795AJ\"></sup> and said, “That’s enough for now! You may leave. When I find it convenient, I will send for you.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>At the same time he was hoping that Paul would offer him a bribe, so he sent for him frequently and talked with him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When two years had passed, Felix was succeeded by Porcius Festus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27797AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27797AK\"></sup> but because Felix wanted to grant a favor to the Jews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27797AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27797AL\"></sup> he left Paul in prison.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27797AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27797AM\"></sup>"
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>Three days after arriving in the province, Festus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27798A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27798A\"></sup> went up from Caesarea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27798B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27798B\"></sup> to Jerusalem,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>where the chief priests and the Jewish leaders appeared before him and presented the charges against Paul.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27799C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27799C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They requested Festus, as a favor to them, to have Paul transferred to Jerusalem, for they were preparing an ambush to kill him along the way.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27800D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27800D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Festus answered, “Paul is being held<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27801E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27801E\"></sup> at Caesarea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27801F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27801F\"></sup> and I myself am going there soon.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Let some of your leaders come with me, and if the man has done anything wrong, they can press charges against him there.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>After spending eight or ten days with them, Festus went down to Caesarea. The next day he convened the court<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27803G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27803G\"></sup> and ordered that Paul be brought before him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27803H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27803H\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When Paul came in, the Jews who had come down from Jerusalem stood around him. They brought many serious charges against him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27804I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27804I\"></sup> but they could not prove them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27804J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27804J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Paul made his defense: “I have done nothing wrong against the Jewish law or against the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27805K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27805K\"></sup> or against Caesar.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Festus, wishing to do the Jews a favor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27806L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27806L\"></sup> said to Paul, “Are you willing to go up to Jerusalem and stand trial before me there on these charges?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27806M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27806M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Paul answered: “I am now standing before Caesar’s court, where I ought to be tried. I have not done any wrong to the Jews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27807N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27807N\"></sup> as you yourself know very well.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>If, however, I am guilty of doing anything deserving death, I do not refuse to die. But if the charges brought against me by these Jews are not true, no one has the right to hand me over to them. I appeal to Caesar!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27808O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27808O\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>After Festus had conferred with his council, he declared: “You have appealed to Caesar. To Caesar you will go!”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>A few days later King Agrippa and Bernice arrived at Caesarea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27810P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27810P\"></sup> to pay their respects to Festus.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Since they were spending many days there, Festus discussed Paul’s case with the king. He said: “There is a man here whom Felix left as a prisoner.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27811Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27811Q\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When I went to Jerusalem, the chief priests and the elders of the Jews brought charges against him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27812R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27812R\"></sup> and asked that he be condemned.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“I told them that it is not the Roman custom to hand over anyone before they have faced their accusers and have had an opportunity to defend themselves against the charges.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27813S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27813S\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When they came here with me, I did not delay the case, but convened the court the next day and ordered the man to be brought in.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27814T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27814T\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When his accusers got up to speak, they did not charge him with any of the crimes I had expected.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Instead, they had some points of dispute<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27816U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27816U\"></sup> with him about their own religion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27816V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27816V\"></sup> and about a dead man named Jesus who Paul claimed was alive.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I was at a loss how to investigate such matters; so I asked if he would be willing to go to Jerusalem and stand trial there on these charges.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27817W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27817W\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But when Paul made his appeal to be held over for the Emperor’s decision, I ordered him held until I could send him to Caesar.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27818X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27818X\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Agrippa said to Festus, “I would like to hear this man myself.”He replied, “Tomorrow you will hear him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27819Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27819Y\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The next day Agrippa and Bernice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27820AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27820AA\"></sup> came with great pomp and entered the audience room with the high-ranking military officers and the prominent men of the city. At the command of Festus, Paul was brought in.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Festus said: “King Agrippa, and all who are present with us, you see this man! The whole Jewish community<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27821AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27821AB\"></sup> has petitioned me about him in Jerusalem and here in Caesarea, shouting that he ought not to live any longer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27821AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27821AC\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>I found he had done nothing deserving of death,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27822AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27822AD\"></sup> but because he made his appeal to the Emperor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27822AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27822AE\"></sup> I decided to send him to Rome.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But I have nothing definite to write to His Majesty about him. Therefore I have brought him before all of you, and especially before you, King Agrippa, so that as a result of this investigation I may have something to write.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For I think it is unreasonable to send a prisoner on to Rome without specifying the charges against him.”"
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>Then Agrippa said to Paul, “You have permission to speak for yourself.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27825A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27825A\"></sup>So Paul motioned with his hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27825B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27825B\"></sup> and began his defense:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“King Agrippa, I consider myself fortunate to stand before you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27826C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27826C\"></sup> today as I make my defense against all the accusations of the Jews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27826D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27826D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and especially so because you are well acquainted with all the Jewish customs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27827E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27827E\"></sup> and controversies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27827F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27827F\"></sup> Therefore, I beg you to listen to me patiently.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“The Jewish people all know the way I have lived ever since I was a child,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27828G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27828G\"></sup> from the beginning of my life in my own country, and also in Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They have known me for a long time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27829H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27829H\"></sup> and can testify, if they are willing, that I conformed to the strictest sect<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27829I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27829I\"></sup> of our religion, living as a Pharisee.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27829J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27829J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And now it is because of my hope<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27830K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27830K\"></sup> in what God has promised our ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27830L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27830L\"></sup> that I am on trial today.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>This is the promise our twelve tribes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27831M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27831M\"></sup> are hoping to see fulfilled as they earnestly serve God day and night.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27831N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27831N\"></sup> King Agrippa, it is because of this hope that these Jews are accusing me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27831O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27831O\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Why should any of you consider it incredible that God raises the dead?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27832P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27832P\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“I too was convinced<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27833Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27833Q\"></sup> that I ought to do all that was possible to oppose<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27833R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27833R\"></sup> the name of Jesus of Nazareth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27833S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27833S\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And that is just what I did in Jerusalem. On the authority of the chief priests I put many of the Lord’s people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27834T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27834T\"></sup> in prison,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27834U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27834U\"></sup> and when they were put to death, I cast my vote against them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27834V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27834V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Many a time I went from one synagogue to another to have them punished,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27835W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27835W\"></sup> and I tried to force them to blaspheme. I was so obsessed with persecuting them that I even hunted them down in foreign cities.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“On one of these journeys I was going to Damascus with the authority and commission of the chief priests.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>About noon, King Agrippa, as I was on the road, I saw a light from heaven, brighter than the sun, blazing around me and my companions.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>We all fell to the ground, and I heard a voice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27838X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27838X\"></sup> saying to me in Aramaic,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27838Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27838Y\"></sup> <span class=\"woj\">‘Saul, Saul, why do you persecute me? It is hard for you to kick against the goads.’</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Then I asked, ‘Who are you, Lord?’“ <span class=\"woj\">‘I am Jesus, whom you are persecuting,’</span> the Lord replied.",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>‘Now get up and stand on your feet.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27840Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27840Z\"></sup> I have appeared to you to appoint you as a servant and as a witness of what you have seen and will see of me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27840AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27840AA\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I will rescue you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27841AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27841AB\"></sup> from your own people and from the Gentiles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27841AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27841AC\"></sup> I am sending you to them</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>to open their eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27842AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27842AD\"></sup> and turn them from darkness to light,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27842AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27842AE\"></sup> and from the power of Satan to God, so that they may receive forgiveness of sins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27842AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27842AF\"></sup> and a place among those who are sanctified by faith in me.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27842AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27842AG\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“So then, King Agrippa, I was not disobedient<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27843AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27843AH\"></sup> to the vision from heaven.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>First to those in Damascus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27844AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27844AI\"></sup> then to those in Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27844AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27844AJ\"></sup> and in all Judea, and then to the Gentiles,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27844AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27844AK\"></sup> I preached that they should repent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27844AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27844AL\"></sup> and turn to God and demonstrate their repentance by their deeds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27844AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27844AM\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>That is why some Jews seized me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27845AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27845AN\"></sup> in the temple courts and tried to kill me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27845AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27845AO\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But God has helped me to this very day; so I stand here and testify to small and great alike. I am saying nothing beyond what the prophets and Moses said would happen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27846AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27846AP\"></sup>—",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>that the Messiah would suffer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27847AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27847AQ\"></sup> and, as the first to rise from the dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27847AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27847AR\"></sup> would bring the message of light to his own people and to the Gentiles.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27847AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27847AS\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>At this point Festus interrupted Paul’s defense. “You are out of your mind,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27848AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27848AT\"></sup> Paul!” he shouted. “Your great learning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27848AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27848AU\"></sup> is driving you insane.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“I am not insane, most excellent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27849AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27849AV\"></sup> Festus,” Paul replied. “What I am saying is true and reasonable.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The king is familiar with these things,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27850AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27850AW\"></sup> and I can speak freely to him. I am convinced that none of this has escaped his notice, because it was not done in a corner.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>King Agrippa, do you believe the prophets? I know you do.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Agrippa said to Paul, “Do you think that in such a short time you can persuade me to be a Christian?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27852AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27852AX\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Paul replied, “Short time or long—I pray to God that not only you but all who are listening to me today may become what I am, except for these chains.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27853AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27853AY\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The king rose, and with him the governor and Bernice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27854AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27854AZ\"></sup> and those sitting with them.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>After they left the room, they began saying to one another, “This man is not doing anything that deserves death or imprisonment.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27855BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27855BA\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Agrippa said to Festus, “This man could have been set free<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27856BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27856BB\"></sup> if he had not appealed to Caesar.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27856BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27856BC\"></sup>"
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>When it was decided that we<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27857A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27857A\"></sup> would sail for Italy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27857B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27857B\"></sup> Paul and some other prisoners were handed over to a centurion named Julius, who belonged to the Imperial Regiment.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27857C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27857C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>We boarded a ship from Adramyttium about to sail for ports along the coast of the province of Asia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27858D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27858D\"></sup> and we put out to sea. Aristarchus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27858E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27858E\"></sup> a Macedonian<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27858F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27858F\"></sup> from Thessalonica,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27858G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27858G\"></sup> was with us.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The next day we landed at Sidon;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27859H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27859H\"></sup> and Julius, in kindness to Paul,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27859I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27859I\"></sup> allowed him to go to his friends so they might provide for his needs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27859J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27859J\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>From there we put out to sea again and passed to the lee of Cyprus because the winds were against us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27860K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27860K\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When we had sailed across the open sea off the coast of Cilicia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27861L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27861L\"></sup> and Pamphylia,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27861M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27861M\"></sup> we landed at Myra in Lycia.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>There the centurion found an Alexandrian ship<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27862N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27862N\"></sup> sailing for Italy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27862O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27862O\"></sup> and put us on board.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>We made slow headway for many days and had difficulty arriving off Cnidus. When the wind did not allow us to hold our course,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27863P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27863P\"></sup> we sailed to the lee of Crete,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27863Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27863Q\"></sup> opposite Salmone.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>We moved along the coast with difficulty and came to a place called Fair Havens, near the town of Lasea.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Much time had been lost, and sailing had already become dangerous because by now it was after the Day of Atonement.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27865R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27865R\"></sup> So Paul warned them,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Men, I can see that our voyage is going to be disastrous and bring great loss to ship and cargo, and to our own lives also.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27866S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27866S\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the centurion, instead of listening to what Paul said, followed the advice of the pilot and of the owner of the ship.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Since the harbor was unsuitable to winter in, the majority decided that we should sail on, hoping to reach Phoenix and winter there. This was a harbor in Crete,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27868T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27868T\"></sup> facing both southwest and northwest.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When a gentle south wind began to blow, they saw their opportunity; so they weighed anchor and sailed along the shore of Crete.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Before very long, a wind of hurricane force,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27870U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27870U\"></sup> called the Northeaster, swept down from the island.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The ship was caught by the storm and could not head into the wind; so we gave way to it and were driven along.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>As we passed to the lee of a small island called Cauda, we were hardly able to make the lifeboat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27872V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27872V\"></sup> secure,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>so the men hoisted it aboard. Then they passed ropes under the ship itself to hold it together. Because they were afraid they would run aground<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27873W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27873W\"></sup> on the sandbars of Syrtis, they lowered the sea anchor and let the ship be driven along.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>We took such a violent battering from the storm that the next day they began to throw the cargo overboard.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27874X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27874X\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>On the third day, they threw the ship’s tackle overboard with their own hands.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When neither sun nor stars appeared for many days and the storm continued raging, we finally gave up all hope of being saved.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>After they had gone a long time without food, Paul stood up before them and said: “Men, you should have taken my advice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27877Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27877Y\"></sup> not to sail from Crete;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27877Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27877Z\"></sup> then you would have spared yourselves this damage and loss.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But now I urge you to keep up your courage,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27878AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27878AA\"></sup> because not one of you will be lost; only the ship will be destroyed.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Last night an angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27879AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27879AB\"></sup> of the God to whom I belong and whom I serve<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27879AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27879AC\"></sup> stood beside me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27879AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27879AD\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and said, ‘Do not be afraid, Paul. You must stand trial before Caesar;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27880AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27880AE\"></sup> and God has graciously given you the lives of all who sail with you.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27880AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27880AF\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So keep up your courage,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27881AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27881AG\"></sup> men, for I have faith in God that it will happen just as he told me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27881AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27881AH\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Nevertheless, we must run aground<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27882AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27882AI\"></sup> on some island.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27882AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27882AJ\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>On the fourteenth night we were still being driven across the Adriatic Sea, when about midnight the sailors sensed they were approaching land.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They took soundings and found that the water was a hundred and twenty feet deep. A short time later they took soundings again and found it was ninety feet deep.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Fearing that we would be dashed against the rocks, they dropped four anchors from the stern and prayed for daylight.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>In an attempt to escape from the ship, the sailors let the lifeboat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27886AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27886AK\"></sup> down into the sea, pretending they were going to lower some anchors from the bow.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Paul said to the centurion and the soldiers, “Unless these men stay with the ship, you cannot be saved.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27887AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27887AL\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So the soldiers cut the ropes that held the lifeboat and let it drift away.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Just before dawn Paul urged them all to eat. “For the last fourteen days,” he said, “you have been in constant suspense and have gone without food—you haven’t eaten anything.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now I urge you to take some food. You need it to survive. Not one of you will lose a single hair from his head.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27890AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27890AM\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>After he said this, he took some bread and gave thanks to God in front of them all. Then he broke it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27891AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27891AN\"></sup> and began to eat.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>They were all encouraged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27892AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27892AO\"></sup> and ate some food themselves.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Altogether there were 276 of us on board.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>When they had eaten as much as they wanted, they lightened the ship by throwing the grain into the sea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27894AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27894AP\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When daylight came, they did not recognize the land, but they saw a bay with a sandy beach,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27895AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27895AQ\"></sup> where they decided to run the ship aground if they could.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Cutting loose the anchors,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27896AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27896AR\"></sup> they left them in the sea and at the same time untied the ropes that held the rudders. Then they hoisted the foresail to the wind and made for the beach.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>But the ship struck a sandbar and ran aground. The bow stuck fast and would not move, and the stern was broken to pieces by the pounding of the surf.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27897AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27897AS\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The soldiers planned to kill the prisoners to prevent any of them from swimming away and escaping.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>But the centurion wanted to spare Paul’s life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27899AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27899AT\"></sup> and kept them from carrying out their plan. He ordered those who could swim to jump overboard first and get to land.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The rest were to get there on planks or on other pieces of the ship. In this way everyone reached land safely.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27900AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27900AU\"></sup>"
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>Once safely on shore, we<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27901A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27901A\"></sup> found out that the island<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27901B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27901B\"></sup> was called Malta.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The islanders showed us unusual kindness. They built a fire and welcomed us all because it was raining and cold.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Paul gathered a pile of brushwood and, as he put it on the fire, a viper, driven out by the heat, fastened itself on his hand.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the islanders saw the snake hanging from his hand,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27904C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27904C\"></sup> they said to each other, “This man must be a murderer; for though he escaped from the sea, the goddess Justice has not allowed him to live.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27904D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27904D\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But Paul shook the snake off into the fire and suffered no ill effects.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27905E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27905E\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The people expected him to swell up or suddenly fall dead; but after waiting a long time and seeing nothing unusual happen to him, they changed their minds and said he was a god.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27906F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27906F\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>There was an estate nearby that belonged to Publius, the chief official of the island. He welcomed us to his home and showed us generous hospitality for three days.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>His father was sick in bed, suffering from fever and dysentery. Paul went in to see him and, after prayer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27908G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27908G\"></sup> placed his hands on him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27908H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27908H\"></sup> and healed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27908I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27908I\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When this had happened, the rest of the sick on the island came and were cured.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They honored us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27910J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27910J\"></sup> in many ways; and when we were ready to sail, they furnished us with the supplies we needed.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>After three months we put out to sea in a ship that had wintered in the island—it was an Alexandrian ship<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27911K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27911K\"></sup> with the figurehead of the twin gods Castor and Pollux.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>We put in at Syracuse and stayed there three days.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>From there we set sail and arrived at Rhegium. The next day the south wind came up, and on the following day we reached Puteoli.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>There we found some brothers and sisters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27914L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27914L\"></sup> who invited us to spend a week with them. And so we came to Rome.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The brothers and sisters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27915M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27915M\"></sup> there had heard that we were coming, and they traveled as far as the Forum of Appius and the Three Taverns to meet us. At the sight of these people Paul thanked God and was encouraged.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When we got to Rome, Paul was allowed to live by himself, with a soldier to guard him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27916N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27916N\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Three days later he called together the local Jewish leaders.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27917O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27917O\"></sup> When they had assembled, Paul said to them: “My brothers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27917P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27917P\"></sup> although I have done nothing against our people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27917Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27917Q\"></sup> or against the customs of our ancestors,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27917R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27917R\"></sup> I was arrested in Jerusalem and handed over to the Romans.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They examined me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27918S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27918S\"></sup> and wanted to release me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27918T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27918T\"></sup> because I was not guilty of any crime deserving death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27918U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27918U\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The Jews objected, so I was compelled to make an appeal to Caesar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27919V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27919V\"></sup> I certainly did not intend to bring any charge against my own people.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For this reason I have asked to see you and talk with you. It is because of the hope of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27920W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27920W\"></sup> that I am bound with this chain.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27920X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27920X\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They replied, “We have not received any letters from Judea concerning you, and none of our people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27921Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27921Y\"></sup> who have come from there has reported or said anything bad about you.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But we want to hear what your views are, for we know that people everywhere are talking against this sect.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27922Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27922Z\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They arranged to meet Paul on a certain day, and came in even larger numbers to the place where he was staying. He witnessed to them from morning till evening, explaining about the kingdom of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27923AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27923AA\"></sup> and from the Law of Moses and from the Prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27923AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27923AB\"></sup> he tried to persuade them about Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27923AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27923AC\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Some were convinced by what he said, but others would not believe.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27924AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27924AD\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They disagreed among themselves and began to leave after Paul had made this final statement: “The Holy Spirit spoke the truth to your ancestors when he said<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27925AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27925AE\"></sup> through Isaiah the prophet:",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“‘Go to this people and say,“You will be ever hearing but never understanding;you will be ever seeing but never perceiving.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For this people’s heart has become calloused;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27927AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27927AF\"></sup>they hardly hear with their ears,and they have closed their eyes.Otherwise they might see with their eyes,hear with their ears,understand with their heartsand turn, and I would heal them.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27927AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27927AG\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“Therefore I want you to know that God’s salvation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27928AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27928AH\"></sup> has been sent to the Gentiles,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27928AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27928AI\"></sup> and they will listen!”<sup class=\"versenum\">[29] </sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For two whole years Paul stayed there in his own rented house and welcomed all who came to see him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He proclaimed the kingdom of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27931AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27931AJ\"></sup> and taught about the Lord Jesus Christ—with all boldness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27931AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27931AK\"></sup> and without hindrance!"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;